{"id": "35136", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35136", "title": "Wand of Apprenti", "text": "The Wand of Apprenti is a magical &lt;a href=\"wand\"&gt;wand&lt;/a&gt; that is only available for owners of the &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Stronghold\"&gt;Mage Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nStatistics.\nWhen activated, the &lt;a href=\"wand\"&gt;wand&lt;/a&gt; will be drained of 1 charge and randomly cast one of the three spells &lt;a href=\"Cone%20of%20Cold\"&gt;Cone of Cold&lt;/a&gt; (with a chance of 35%), &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt; (with a chance of 36%) or &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt; (with a chance of 29%). When drained of all charges, the wand becomes useless.\nLocations.\nThe Wand of the Apprenti can only be acquired as part of the &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Stronghold\"&gt;Mage Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; quests. It is one of the three magical items \u2013 alongside the &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20of%20CHARNAME\"&gt;Dagger of CHARNAME&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20the%20Princes%20%2B1\"&gt;Ring of the Princes +1&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; can request that their three new apprentices &lt;a href=\"Morul\"&gt;Morul&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Larz\"&gt;Larz&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Nara\"&gt;Nara&lt;/a&gt; attempt to complete to begin their magical training."}
{"id": "8905", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8905", "title": "Wand of Cloudkill", "text": "Wand of Cloudkill is a wand which can be used to launch a projectile at an area designated by the user within range. The projectile flies forth to the selected location and then it bursts out a billowing cloud of toxic gas. This item appears in and .\nGameplay.\nThis wand does not actually cast a &lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt; spell but emulates it. \nThe wand has a range of 60', an area effect of 20' radius and can target a single location which will be selected with the player's cursor. \nIt fires with a speed of 0 (zero), so it is almost instantly discharged. \nAll of the Wand's effects are set at Spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 5. The wand is coded as an Invocation School and is \"Battleground\" secondary type. \nAll of the wand's effects can be blocked by magic resistance, but it bypasses &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt will &lt;a href=\"Slay\"&gt;Slay&lt;/a&gt; nonimmune 1-4 HD creatures instantly. 5-6 HD creatures must make a saving throw each round exposed or they too will be killed. Any creature within the cloud is exposed to 1d10 &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; every round. \nCreatures immune to &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; are protected from the wand's effects and will not be disrupted from spell casting - which was a problem in the original game but fixed in a recent version of the Enhanced Edition.\nOnce deployed, the cloud can't be removed from the battlefield area except by a &lt;a href=\"Wing%20Buffet\"&gt;Wing Buffet&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Zone%20of%20Sweet%20Air\"&gt;Zone of Sweet Air&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "39924", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39924", "title": "Wand of Cloudkill Key", "text": "Wand of Cloudkill Key is used to disarm an otherwise permanent trap in &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon%202nd%20Floor\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon 2nd Floor&lt;/a&gt;. When used for this purpose, it changes into a &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Cloudkill\"&gt;Wand of Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt; with 1 charge."}
{"id": "27875", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27875", "title": "Wand of Cursing", "text": "Wand of Cursing is a wand which can be used to make its target &lt;a href=\"Blinded\"&gt;Blind&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Deafness\"&gt;Deaf&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Silenced\"&gt;Mute&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt appears in ' and '. \nAquisition.\nThis item can be found on &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt; and in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Illithid%20Encampment\"&gt;Illithid Encampment&lt;/a&gt; or created by the &lt;a href=\"Wish%23Create%20a%20random%20wand%20in%20the%20caster%27s%20inventory.\"&gt;Wish&lt;/a&gt; spell. \nGameplay.\nThe wand's user places this wand in a \"quick item\" slot, and then selects a single creature target to aim the wand's projectile toward.\nWhen the projectile reaches the target, it is exposed to the wand's spell effects.\nEnemies roll a single &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. spells (no bonuses or penalties) against all three effects combined and, if failed, they'll be blinded, deafened and made mute for 1 turn (10 rounds).\nIf the saving throw is missed, the victim's sprite will render a brief 3D effect and a color glow upon it, as well as three text displays on the combat log reading \"Blinded\", \"Deaf\", and \"Silence\".\nThis item's effects are actually more powerful than the description suggests, as it not only causes deafness, silence and blindness, it also inflicts a cumulative penalty of 4 points to THAC0.\nThat means that on the first failed save, the target will get a total penalty of 8 points to THAC0, not 4, as they'll be inflicted by blindness (that worsens both AC and THAC0 by 4) and the separate THAC0 penalty. \nFurther successful applications will increase the THAC0 penalty by 4; however, the initial THAC0 penalty of 8 is already significant, as it potentially means a reduction of 40% to the enemy's chance to hit your party.\nThe wand's effects can be potentially blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, however as all the internal effects are &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 0, and have no assigned spell school or secondary type - there is no protection afforded by &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; or spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;.\nA target protected by a &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; won't gain any protection against this wand.\nThe wand's debilitating maladies are subject to removal with a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect and certain other specific cures.\nThis item has a maximum of 8 charges when sold and repurchased from vendors.\nThis is also one of the few items in the game that can be used by literally any class/kit, including Wizard Slayers."}
{"id": "3854", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3854", "title": "Wand of Fear", "text": "A Wand of Fear can strike terror in the hearts of enemies within 20 feet of the target, unless a save vs Spell is made with a +2 bonus. Range is 60 feet, despite statistics claiming 100 feet. Allies are not affected, and some enemies are immune to fear. Unless recharged by a merchant, the wand is destroyed when the last charge is expended. Unlike most wands, this one can be used by both arcane and divine casters.\nGameplay.\nEach charge of this wand is aimed at a location in range which will launch a projectile (No. 170) which will not affect the party. \nNon-party creatures in the Area of Effect are exposed to a &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; effect, requiring a saving throw vs. spell (with a +2 bonus). A failed save will cause panic for 100 seconds. The spell effect is of the Enchanter spell school with the secondary type classification of \"Disabling\". \nThe wand's spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; is 4. &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can block its effects. \nAny creature that fails its save will have special 3D graphic effect play over the creature (face on ground - horror), as well as a lighting effect (SHAIR) and color fade. A sound effect also plays."}
{"id": "4162", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4162", "title": "Wand of Fire", "text": "Wands of Fire have two abilities instead of one, when compared to other wands. This is one of the more powerful wands, but also more expensive. This wand has the ability to conjure a fireball, like the\u00a03rd level spell &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;, and to send a column of flame towards the target, like the 2nd level spell &lt;a href=\"Agannazar%27s%20Scorcher\"&gt;Agannazar's Scorcher&lt;/a&gt;. For both abilities a save roll vs wands for half damage can be made. But, like all other wands, it has a limited quantity of charges, and should it run out in any one of its abilities it will destroy itself, even if the other ability still had charges remaining.\nFireball ability.\nThe Fireball ability will inflict 6d6 points of &lt;a href=\"fire%20damage\"&gt;fire damage&lt;/a&gt; that will affect friend and foe alike who are in the 15-foot radius from where the fireball exploded into a wave of flames. A save roll vs wands for half damage can be made. The range is 90 ft.\nAgannazar's Scorcher ability.\nThe Agannazar's Scorcher ability sends a column of flame towards the target, inflicting 6d6 +6 points of fire damage (Save vs Wands for half), while the original spell can inflict only 3d6 points of damage (No save). Compared to the Wizard's spell version, the wand's scorcher jet is much longer in length (2X40 feet), almost three times lengthier.\nNote: The spell description states that the area of effect is 1 creature, but in fact the jet of flame inflicts damage to anyone, friend or foe, standing in the path of the flame jet between the caster and the target. The one-creature term is technically correct for target selection purposes. If the target has &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; active, it will reflect part of the scorcher back to damage the wand user.\nLocations.\nIn all games it can be found as &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt;\nNotes.\nSome of these wands come with a fixed number of charges, and for each charge you can pick either ability. The Wand of Fire that Erdane sells comes with 20 charges of Fireball and 1 charge of Agannazar's Scorcher. When that 1 charge of Agannazar's Scorcher is used, the wand is destroyed, no matter how many charges of Fireball remain.\nThe wands description \"..column of flame..\" is awkward usage, as a column is generally defined in most cases with a vertical perspective, and this wand's scorcher is using a lateral orientation."}
