{"id": "3800", "revid": "284599", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3800", "title": "Wand of Frost", "text": "Wands of Frost are charged with magical cold energy that will instantly drain the heat from any creature with potentially debilitating effects. Be careful using this when dealing a killing blow, as this wand has been known to completely disintegrate the body, destroying any possible loot.\nNote: The wand behaves differently in BG and BGII for both Effect and Area.\u00a0In BG the column\u00a0is \"party friendly\", only affects the target, and can be cast from the back ranks.\u00a0In BGIIEE\u00a0the cone will damage allies that are within it."}
{"id": "39920", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39920", "title": "Wand of Frost Key", "text": "Wand of Frost Key is used to disarm an otherwise permanent trap in &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon%202nd%20Floor\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon 2nd Floor&lt;/a&gt;. When used for this purpose, it changes into a &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Frost\"&gt;Wand of Frost&lt;/a&gt; with 1 charge."}
{"id": "45648", "revid": "272808", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45648", "title": "Wand of Glitterdust", "text": "Wand of Glitterdust is a wand which can cast a wand version of the &lt;a href=\"Glitterdust\"&gt;Glitterdust&lt;/a&gt; spell to detect invisible creatures. It is found at some crystals in the northeastern part of &lt;a href=\"Resurrection%20Gorge\"&gt;Resurrection Gorge&lt;/a&gt;. It is one of the many ways to detect &lt;a href=\"Xachrimos\"&gt;Xachrimos&lt;/a&gt; if the party has no way to cast spell which can detect invisible creatures.\nGameplay.\nThe wand's version of Glitterdust is unique and has some different effects than the spell version.\nThe wand holder may expend a charge from the wand and select a location for the Glitterdust effect to spread from. \nThe wand fires a projectile (150-Sparkle Area Gold (SPKLARGO)). \nWhen the rapidly moving projectile reaches the point designated by the operator (up to a 45' distance from the wand user maximum) the sparkling area of effect manifests in a 15-foot radius from the target spot.\nAll creatures (including the party) in the area of effect are exposed to the sparking particles unless a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell is made. If the save is made the wand has no effect on that particular creature.\nIf the saving throw check is failed, then the creature:\n- Suffers a &lt;a href=\"Blindness\"&gt;Blindness&lt;/a&gt; effect lasting 4 rounds. A text string will display \"Blinded\".\n- If hidden, the creature is revealed (including normal and improved invisibility, sanctuary and Hide in Shadows). \n- The creature is also unable to attain being hidden for 4 rounds (when the glittering particles wear off). \nThis wand's effects are classified as a \"Conjuration\" spell school, and a \"Battleground\" secondary type. The individual effects of glittering dust are considered non-magical and therefore can't be affected by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects or &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;. However, the effects are given a 2 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt;, and thus can be blocked by a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4158", "revid": "272809", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4158", "title": "Wand of Lightning", "text": "Wands of Lightning can be used to discharge bolts of lightning, like the spell &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt;, which does also damage to allies if they cross path with the lightning bolt.\u00a0 The wand's effect is different depending on whether \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" or \"\" is being played. This wand has a limited number of charges and will be destroyed when it runs out; wands can be \"recharged\" by selling them to a vendor and purchasing them back. Obviously, ensure the wand has at least one charge remaining if you intend to sell it.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThe wand discharges a single lightning bolt, which deals 6d6 electrical damage. It must be cast on a creature, and targets struck by the bolt can Save vs. Wand to take half damage. The bolt will bounce off of walls and other objects until expended.\nIn \"\".\nThe wand discharges six lightning bolts simultaneously, which deal 3d6 electrical damage each. When the wand is used, the user must select six targets; the same creature can be selected multiple times (e.g., all six bolts may be aimed at one creature). Targets struck by a bolt can Save vs. Wand to take half damage. Each bolt will bounce off of walls and other objects until expended.\nIn the BG2 EE version of the wand, the internal op-coding of the item has been updated. It functions almost the same as the basic SoA game item. It has a range of 45-feet, bypasses mirror image, has a level 3 spell power, and is affected by magic resistance. The item also has a safeguard opcode to prevent the user from targeting themself with 1-6 bolts. Each projectile lightning bolt on a target will get a separate saving throw to determine damage. The wand has a maximum capacity of 50 charges in the EE update."}
