{"id": "3426", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3426", "title": "Wand of Magic Missiles", "text": "A Wand of Magic Missiles is a type available in all games of the .\nIt can be utilized by members of all &lt;a href=\"classes\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; except the &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20Slayer\"&gt;Wizard Slayer&lt;/a&gt;, provided they have at least 9 &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe wand has a maximum capacity of 100 charges, although when a wand is acquired, it may not be completely charged. Stores sell it at per charge; a price further adjusted following the &lt;a href=\"shop%20price\"&gt;shop price&lt;/a&gt; formula.\nThe user places this wand in their \"Quick Item\" slot, then using the targeting cursor to select an individual creature to aim the missile towards.\nThe energy projectile will automatically hit the target, and a brief lighting effect and color fade will render on the target's sprite.\n1d4+1 &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt; is applied to the creature, although several factors can make this missile ineffective.\n&lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can block the wand's missile, as well as the lowest spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;.\nA target with an active &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt; will be protected, or with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Evocation&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt; will block the missile as well.\nThe internal coding of this wand's effects is assigned an Evocation spell school, Offensive damage secondary type, and has a 1 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt;."}
