{"id": "4161", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4161", "title": "Wand of Monster Summoning", "text": "Wands of Monster Summoning can be used to summon monsters. It has the same power as the &lt;a href=\"Monster%20Summoning%20II\"&gt;Monster Summoning II&lt;/a&gt; spell, it will summon monsters with a total of 12 hit dice. The summoned monsters remain for 2 turns or until they are slain. When there are no enemies to attack and the user of the wand may communicate with them, they may be used for other services. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, , and . Only &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"bard\"&gt;bard&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;s may use this wand."}
{"id": "4053", "revid": "284600", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4053", "title": "Wand of Paralyzation", "text": "A Wand of Paralyzation is used to quickly &lt;a href=\"stun\"&gt;stun&lt;/a&gt; the target.\nDescription.\nGeneral description\n&lt;a href=\"Identify\"&gt;Identified&lt;/a&gt; description\nGameplay.\nThe wand has a range of 100' and can target a single creature with each charge. \nIt fires with a speed of 0 (zero), so it is almost instantly discharged. \nAll of the Wand's effects are set at Spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 4. The wand is coded as an Enchanter School and type is \"Disabling\" secondary type. \nAll of the wand's effects can be blocked by magic resistance, but it bypasses &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;. \nIf the target is hit by the wand's projectile and a saving throw is missed, then the target will briefly glow, A sound effect will play, the target will be suffer a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; status effect. a text message string stating \"stunned\" will be shown in the combat box. After 60 seconds the creature will no longer be stunned. \nThis Stun effect can be removed by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel&lt;/a&gt; effects. Any spell protections that can block a level 4 spell power effect can prevent the wand from affecting the protected creature, examples include a &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;. Also, creatures immune to this level of spell and item effects (level 4 in this wand's case) are also immune to this wand, for example a &lt;a href=\"Rakshasa\"&gt;Rakshasa&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4167", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4167", "title": "Wand of Polymorphing", "text": "This wand is used to polymorph a creature into a squirrel. The wand emits a thin, green beam that goes towards the creature. The creature then must make save roll vs. wands or be polymorphed into a squirrel, which lasts until dispelled. Like most wands, this item has a limited amount of charges.\nGameplay.\nThe wand is aimed at a single detected target and launches a projectile (209) [which is the same one used by the &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate\"&gt;Disintegrate&lt;/a&gt; spell]. The projectile applies the &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20Other\"&gt;polymormph other&lt;/a&gt; effect to the target creature.\nThe target creature is allowed a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Wands to negate this effect. &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can also block it, as well as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20protections%20type\"&gt;Spell protections type&lt;/a&gt; defenses, such as &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, that can deflect or absorb a &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 4 effect. \nThe wand's effect is not categorized as any spell school or secondary type, so &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; won't affect it.\nIf the saving throw is failed and the wand's effect isn't blocked in some fashion, then the target is transformed into a &lt;a href=\"squirrel\"&gt;squirrel&lt;/a&gt;. This effect is basically permanent until a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect can restore the original state.\nLocations.\nIn Baldur's Gate this wand is gained as a possible reward from &lt;a href=\"Voltinabulai\"&gt;Voltine&lt;/a&gt; in the side quest &lt;a href=\"Laerta%20and%20Louise\"&gt;Laerta and Louise&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Northwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Northwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn Baldur's Gate II: Enhanced Edition this item is sold by a wand merchant in the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizard%20Enclave\"&gt;Red Wizard Enclave&lt;/a&gt;, accessible during &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt;'s personal questline."}
{"id": "4157", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4157", "title": "Wand of Sleep", "text": "The Wand of Sleep is available in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate (game)&lt;/a&gt;, , and as well as .\nGameplay.\nThe magical powers of this wand only affect hostile creatures in its target area if they have at most 4 Hit Dice. \nThe wand's effects are categorized as an \"Enchantment\" spell school and \"Disabling\" secondary type.\nA &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Wands will negate the &lt;a href=\"Sleep%20%28Status%20Effect%29\"&gt;Sleep (Status Effect)&lt;/a&gt;. A missed saving throw puts the creature to sleep for 2 turns (20 rounds).\n&lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; can block the wand's sleep effect.\nCreatures that fall asleep will be &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt;, are interrupted if they were casting, and can no longer perform any actions. They will not wake up when damaged.\nHostile &lt;a href=\"Elf\"&gt;Elf&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Half-elf\"&gt;Half-elf&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; creatures will receive their racial sleep resistance chance versus this wand.\nFor the most part, in Baldur's Gate II hostile creatures with 4 HD or less are restricted to a few minor &lt;a href=\"Sahuagin\"&gt;Sahuagin&lt;/a&gt; enemies, and otherwise the wand's use is very limited.\nA wand can take up to 100 charges (though rarely seen). Its value of puts the price per charge at . This can be used to calculate the number of charges one can expect when buying one from a merchant. Take note to account for &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Charisma\"&gt;Charisma&lt;/a&gt; based modifications as well as the &lt;a href=\"Game%20Terminology%23S\"&gt;store markup&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhere to obtain.\nBaldur's Gate and Tales of the Sword Coast.\nThis Wand is carried by the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20Wizard\"&gt;Cult Wizard&lt;/a&gt; who steals &lt;a href=\"Soultaker%20Dagger\"&gt;Soultaker&lt;/a&gt; from you, to bring &lt;a href=\"Aec%27Letec\"&gt;Aec'Letec&lt;/a&gt; to the Main Material Plane again.\nThrone of Bhaal and Baldur's Gate II: Enhanced Edition.\nIt can be looted from the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt;. It is the only known occurrence of this wand in the 2nd game series."}
{"id": "22603", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22603", "title": "Wand of Spell Striking", "text": "A powerful wand which the user can choose to fire a charge to manifest either &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt; spell effects.\nBoth of these wand abilities are of the &lt;a href=\"Magic%20attack%20type\"&gt;Magic attack type&lt;/a&gt; in only, meaning they will not penetrate &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Shield\"&gt;Spell Shield&lt;/a&gt;. Each charge used by the wand will be blocked by Spell Shield and consume the Spell Shield. This is a fix to an oversight in the basic game.\nThe Pierce Magic spell belongs to the category.\nDescription.\nSTATISTICS:\nCharge abilities:\n- Breach: Dispels all specific and combat protections on 1 target, range 40 feet.\n- Pierce Magic: Lowers target's Magic Resistance by 20% for 2 turns and removes one spell protection from target. Range is 40 feet.\nRequires: 9 Intelligence.\nWeight: 1.\nGameplay.\nThis wand instantly casts a Breach or Pierce Magic spell effect (not an actual Breach or Pierce Magic Spell). Both effects are coded as Abjuration School and Magic Attack Type.\nThe basic game:\nBreach in the basic game can be blocked by Spell Shield (which is then consumed). This wand's Breach effect was miscoded, and Spell Shield does not work against it.\nBreach in the basic game cannot affect creatures immune to level 5 spells, like a Lich or Rakshasa. This means that there was no way to ever Breach a Lich, including using this wand.\nBreach or Pierce Magic cannot penetrate a Protection from Magic scroll.\nThe EE game:\nAll of the Breach and Pierce magic rules are the same as the basic game, however, this wand is now fixed and coded properly.\nSee the &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; Spell Description page for further details, including Mod content for Breach.\nNotes.\nThis wand exists in the code of \"\", but makes no in-game appearance."}
{"id": "39921", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39921", "title": "Wand of Summoning Key", "text": "Wand of Summoning Key is used to disarm a trap in &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon%202nd%20Floor\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon 2nd Floor&lt;/a&gt;. When used for this purpose, it changes into a &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Monster%20Summoning\"&gt;Wand of Monster Summoning&lt;/a&gt; with 1 charge.\nNote that unlike the other wand traps that can be triggered multiple times, the one associated with this wand disappears if triggered. However, the key can still be used and converted to a wand even if the summoning trap is gone."}
