{"id": "49380", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49380", "title": "Warden Thrall", "text": "A Warden Thrall is a &lt;a href=\"Fighter\"&gt;Fighter&lt;/a&gt; who protects the &lt;a href=\"Planar%20Prison\"&gt;Planar Prison&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Prison%20Warden\"&gt;Warden&lt;/a&gt; directly. They are found only in the Warden's immediate vicinity.\nGameplay.\nThere are three of these elven male warriors, who are subjugated with \"Thrall Collars\". The warriors stand ready close to the &lt;a href=\"Prison%20Warden\"&gt;Prison Warden&lt;/a&gt;. They will be hostile to the party and can move toward a detected party member to engage in close quarters melee combat with their enchanted long sword. They are armored with chain mail and a medium shield. \nShould the &lt;a href=\"Mastery%20Orb\"&gt;Mastery Orb&lt;/a&gt; be placed in the crucible and deactivated, these thralls will no longer be under the command of the planar prison Warden or Master of Thralls and be neutral toward the party and hostile to the prison controllers. Although they can't be controlled by the party, their enemy is also the party's enemy.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the warrior with a new default SCS AI script for smarter tactical behavior. Weapon proficiencies are changed, with 5 pips in longsword, and 2 pips in sword and shield fighting style. This results in improved THAC0, APR, damage and armor class."}
