{"id": "37069", "revid": "3077225", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37069", "title": "Wardstone", "text": "The Bridgefort Wardstone is an enchanted token that grants its bearer and anyone with them the ability to use the teleportation circle that connects &lt;a href=\"Bridgefort\"&gt;Bridgefort&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt;. Prior to the Shining Crusade of &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar Argent&lt;/a&gt;, it was stolen from Bridgefort by a cultist of &lt;a href=\"Cyric\"&gt;Cyric&lt;/a&gt; from the nearby &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Ruined Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;. When encountered at &lt;a href=\"Troll%20Claw%20Woods\"&gt;Troll Claw Woods&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; will instruct &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to seek out the Wardstone and use it to enter Bridgefort.\nLocation.\nThe Bridgefort Wardstone is in the possession of &lt;a href=\"High%20Priestess%20Akanna\"&gt;High Priestess Akanna&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Ruined Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;, and can be looted from her body after she is killed."}
{"id": "52819", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52819", "title": "Wardstone (Siege of Dragonspear)", "text": "This Wardstone is held by &lt;a href=\"Akanna\"&gt;Akanna&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Cyric\"&gt;Temple of Cyric&lt;/a&gt;. The wardstone allows &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to move from &lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Bridgefort\"&gt;Bridgefort&lt;/a&gt;.\nUse.\nClicking on the circle of runes to the east of Bridgefort in the Boareskyr Bridge, near the broken bridge, while you have the wardstone in your &lt;a href=\"Inventory\"&gt;Inventory&lt;/a&gt;, allows the party to appear in Bridgefort.\nThe Crusade.\nOnce obtained, you can speak with &lt;a href=\"The%20Crusade\"&gt;The Crusade&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Kharm\"&gt;Kharm&lt;/a&gt; who will ask you to lower Bridgefort's drawbridge. If you agree to it, it enables the &lt;a href=\"Down%20With%20the%20Drawbridge\"&gt;Down With the Drawbridge&lt;/a&gt; quest."}
{"id": "40661", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40661", "title": "Wardstone (Watcher's Keep Altar Level)", "text": "Gameplay.\nBoth of these Wardstones can be found in containers/shelving in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Altar%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Altar Level&lt;/a&gt;. Based on the clues in the description the player might associate their possession with the phrase \"two towers\" and the golem picture to correlate with the two &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20Golem\"&gt;Guardian Golem&lt;/a&gt; creatures found in the locked chamber with the sarcophagus. Or maybe not.\nRegardless, if the party has one or two of these wardstones in the inventory, then the Guardian Golem(s) won't activate when disturbing (clicking on) the sarcophagus. The golems will also become hostile if attacked, even with the wardstones. \nThe wardstones serve no other game purpose. Keeping them in the inventory after exploring the sarcophagus will just take up space, and they can't be sold.\nOf course, it's also possible that the party may not ever take either of the wardstones into their possession, and they'll never know what they can do, and perhaps ended up battling the Guardian Golems anyway. "}
