{"id": "56670", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56670", "title": "Watcher's Keep (Quest)", "text": "Watcher's Keep (Quest) is a side quest available and .\nThe quest is a \"side quest\" because all content in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; is optional and not mandatory to complete the main story - however, this quest is mandatory if attempting to complete the Watcher's Keep storyline.\nAcquisition.\nThe quest is initially registered in the player's journal by engaging with the &lt;a href=\"Odren\"&gt;Odren&lt;/a&gt;, the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Vigil%20Knight\"&gt;Vigil Knight&lt;/a&gt; group at the exterior of &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;.\nJournal entries.\nRegistering the quest.\nIf the player agrees to assist the Vigil Knights with entering the keep and fixing the seals within to keep a \"great evil\" imprisoned, then the quest is registered into the journal, as follows:\nIf Gorion's Ward declines to help, then the Knights remain and can be spoken to at a later time, but there is no way for the party to enter Watcher's Keep until they agree to help the Knights. Declining the quest results in the following Journal Entry:\nOdren instructs the party.\nThe party is also instructed to get background information from &lt;a href=\"Brother%20Pol\"&gt;Brother Pol&lt;/a&gt; and some necessary items before entry into the keep can be made. At this time another Journal entry update is registered:\nThe party will then make its way through the keep's various dungeon levels, one by one, until it finally gains access to the last level. There are no specific Journal entries registered for the \"Watcher's Keep\" questline of any consequence during the adventuring and exploration of these five levels, although there will be other side quests introduced, such as:"}
