{"id": "55857", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55857", "title": "Watcher's Keep \u2013 Ka'rashur (AR3013)", "text": "This is the Watcher's Keep - Ka'rashure area of the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;. This area is available during saga, as early as &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;. It is also available as part of the campaign if playing the original or Enhanced Edition game.\nArea description.\nThis room only has two portals on the north and south. The architectural and decor are similar to a room likely already &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20-%20Tahazzar%20%28AR3012%29\"&gt;visited&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe slightly sunken circular symbol of helm commands attention in the center of the chamber.\nResting on this dungeon level.\nThere is a random probability of being disturbed by infernal fiends if resting here. \"You are awakened from your rest\" will be shown on the combat log, and the enemies can include a &lt;a href=\"Cornugon\"&gt;Cornugon&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Erinyes\"&gt;Erinyes&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Imp\"&gt;Imp&lt;/a&gt; group. \nGameplay.\nThe party arrives on the northern side of this room and is immediately challenged by a Baatezu Pit Fiend &lt;a href=\"Ka%27rashur\"&gt;Ka'rashur&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the party has already accepted the job from &lt;a href=\"Tahazzar\"&gt;Tahazzar&lt;/a&gt; then the devil will sense this and cry out a call to arms leading to hostilities.\nIf not, then there will be some dialogue potential with \"Player1\" (usually this is Gorion's Ward). However, if \"Player1\" is a Paladin, or of lawful good &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;Alignment&lt;/a&gt; then the devil recognizes the taint of goodness, and hostilities will ensue.\nIf those conditions aren't applicable, there will be one more check as the dialogue continues. If \"Player1\" is neutral good alignment, then the fiend will not stomach that virtue either, and fighting will start.\nAssuming none of that occurs, the player can just attack the devils as soon as an applicable dialogue selection is chosen. The party could also strike a deal with the devil and agree to perform a job for Ka'rashur. This leads to the party receiving &lt;a href=\"The%20Blood%20War\"&gt;The Blood War&lt;/a&gt; quest. See that article for more details.\nIf at any time the party is drawn into or chooses to fight the devils here, expect an intense and dangerous fight. Much infernal magic will fly, and all sorts of disabling and hazardous status effects are possible.\nIf the party is triumphant, collect any valuables from the fallen devils. Especially the items recovered from the Pit Fiend. The party is going to need one of those to finish escaping the Maze.\nNotes.\nAs shown on the InfoBox, Ka'rashur's AI script file will initiate spawning of extra devil creatures in this room when hostilities begin. This occurs if the player's game difficulty selection is not less than \"Normal\", and the party's experience level is greater than 16.\nAdditional &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Golem\"&gt;Bone Golem&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cornugon\"&gt;Cornugon&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Velithuu\"&gt;Velithuu&lt;/a&gt; creatures will appear after a slight delay in the battle.\nContainers.\nA hidden niche in the base of a wall pillar may be detected on the eastern side of the chamber. Use precautions before examining it, as one never knows what sorts of traps might be present.\nTake whatever items are desired from the container including:"}
{"id": "40950", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40950", "title": "Watcher's Keep \u2013 Saladrex (Dragon)", "text": "This area is available for exploration in and .\nDescription.\nThe party can enter this area from the southwestern corner of the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Githyanki%20Encampment\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Githyanki Encampment&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere is no map information in the previous area that explains what this area is called or might be.\nThis area doesn't require the \"You must gather your party\" mechanic, and can be entered with one or more characters, allowing the party to be split.\nWhen the party transition to this area, they'll be on a huge descending set of stairs - the area below is well lit - but has a strong musky/gamey odor present in the air.\nResting on this dungeon level.\nIf the party rests in this dungeon area, there is no random chance of a rest encounter that will disturb the party. "}
{"id": "55854", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55854", "title": "Watcher's Keep \u2013 Tieflings (AR3005)", "text": "This is the Watcher's Keep - Tiefling area of the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;. This area is available during saga, as early as &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;. It is also available as part of the campaign if playing the original or Enhanced Edition game.\nArea description.\nThe party has seen this type of room layout and architecture before. \nFour portals with ascending stairs lead to a square shaped floor. The floor is tiled with segmented stones. Four archways are positioned at each staircase. Hanging banners with illuminated symbols are fastened to the archway vertical pillars.\nResting on this dungeon level.\nThere is a random probability of being disturbed by infernal fiends if resting here. \"You are awakened from your rest\" will be shown on the combat log, and the enemies can include a &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Fiend\"&gt;Bone Fiend&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Marilith\"&gt;Marilith&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cornugon\"&gt;Cornugon&lt;/a&gt; group. \nGameplay.\nThe party transitioned into the northern side this area. \nWhen a party member climbs the steps up to the floor above a text will display:\nIt's possible the party has experienced this phenomenon in this maze before, when they visited the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20-%20Wild%20Magic%3F%20%28AR3009%29\"&gt;room with the quasits&lt;/a&gt;.\nAny spell casting here may be affected by a &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Surge\"&gt;Wild Surge&lt;/a&gt;, with potentially random results occurring.\nWithin the room are seen a group of armed humanoids, with features that suggest they are &lt;a href=\"Tiefling\"&gt;Tieflings&lt;/a&gt;. If any party members are detected by the group, the &lt;a href=\"Tiefling%20%28Mage%29\"&gt;Tiefling (Mage)&lt;/a&gt; shouts an alarm, saying:\nThis area of the maze is one of the only places where being hidden or invisible/sanctuaried is effective, as these Tieflings aren't able to &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen the alarm is sounded, a few moments later the group will turn hostile. The two &lt;a href=\"Tiefling%20%28Fighter%29\"&gt;Tiefling (Fighter)&lt;/a&gt; warriors will initiate their &lt;a href=\"Whirlwind%20Attack\"&gt;Whirlwind Attack&lt;/a&gt; innate ability and move forward and attack the closest detected party member. \nAssuming the mage wasn't instantly slain in some manner, then she summons &lt;a href=\"Aranthis\"&gt;Aranthis&lt;/a&gt;, a plane travelling version of a Moon dog to join the Tieflings. \nAlso, a &lt;a href=\"Tiefling%20%28Thief%29\"&gt;Tiefling (Thief)&lt;/a&gt; will quaff a potion and turn invisible, and then advance to attack, possibly with a &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt; opportunity.\nUnless disrupted, the mage will attempt to self-protect with a few buffs, and then begin trying some offensive spell options at eligible targets. This initial preparatory action might go awry with a Wild Surge, or it might not.\nThe Moon dog may also be able to turn Improved Invisible, and initiate a &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; as well. The dog has a biting attack.\nBe aware that the Tiefling magic might Wild Surge just like the party's spells could. This can lead to unpredictable and potentially unforeseen results that could be beneficial or harmful to the casters."}
{"id": "55858", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55858", "title": "Watcher's Keep \u2013 White Dragon Scales (AR3014)", "text": "This is the Watcher's Keep - White Dragon Scales area of the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;. This area is available during saga, as early as &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;. It is also available as part of the campaign if playing the original or Enhanced Edition game.\nArea description.\nThe party has seen this room's architectural layout and decor twice before in the room's with &lt;a href=\"Tahazzar\"&gt;Tahazzar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ka%27rashur\"&gt;Ka'rashur&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe only discernable immediate difference her is the various piles of scattered bones and equipment scattered about the floor.\nResting on this dungeon level.\nThere is a random probability of being disturbed by infernal fiends if resting here. \"You are awakened from your rest\" will be shown on the combat log, and the enemies can include a &lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Wraith\"&gt;Vampiric Wraith&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Devil%20Shade\"&gt;Devil Shade&lt;/a&gt; group. \nGameplay.\nThe party enters this room transiting through the northern portal.\nAttention to the fact that this area has several potentially hazardous traps. It is possible that any movement forward could kill one or more party members. Taking control of the party and micromanaging their movement, perhaps disabling any automatic melee attacking scripts, and similar action could help prevent this. Having a thief that can detect and disarm traps is useful.\nCasting the &lt;a href=\"Find%20Traps\"&gt;Find Traps&lt;/a&gt; spell can be a quick way to at least know where they are.\nUpon entry, the party will observe a creature with an undead appearance positioned further south. The creature is a &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Wraith\"&gt;Demon Wraith&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe demon makes an opening remark in a hollow and chilling voice, saying:\nThis triggers the demon's initial protective spell casting chain and will also cause the appearance of several hostile &lt;a href=\"Slave%20Wraith\"&gt;Slave Wraith&lt;/a&gt; creatures in the chamber.\nThe slaves will occasionally show various text displays that indicate they can't help themselves from attacking and are being forced to obey the demon.\nThe slaves will move toward the closest party member they can detect (they also &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;) and will attack in melee touch weapon range.\nSpell casting will continue from the demon, and it will try and get a &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt; spell completed, and then place a few symbol spells at the nearest party member, or perhaps a &lt;a href=\"Abi-Dalzim%27s%20Horrid%20Wilting\"&gt;Abi-Dalzim's Horrid Wilting&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter that, the demon will advance and melee attack. If the party's XP levels are greater than 16, it will also cast &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate\"&gt;Disintegrate&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Finger%20of%20Death%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Finger of Death (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Domination\"&gt;Domination&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Prismatic%20Spray\"&gt;Prismatic Spray&lt;/a&gt;, repeatedly until it is unable to, or destroyed.\nIf any slave wraiths are still viable when the demon is destroyed, every surviving slave awards . The slaves give thanks for releasing them from their bondage.\nTreasure.\nThere are a number of \"piles\" of loot that can be examined and plundered for treasure in this area. These are ostensibly from fallen adventurers destroyed by the Demon Wraith.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Construction%20for%20Spellcasters\"&gt;Golem Construction for Spellcasters&lt;/a&gt; mod places a rare component, a \"Mithral alloy\", in one of the piles of loot in this room. The alloy can be used by an arcane spell caster to build their own Mithral Golem, assuming other requirements and a special tome are also on-hand."}
