{"id": "23780", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23780", "title": "Werewolf Caverns", "text": "The Werewolf Warrens, also known as the Werewolf Caverns, are a series of warrens underneath the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran%20South\"&gt;Werewolf Village&lt;/a&gt; at the southern end of the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Isle of Balduran&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and their party use these tunnels to make it to &lt;a href=\"Kaishas%20Gan\"&gt;Kaishas Gan&lt;/a&gt;'s boat and escape the Isle of Balduran after &lt;a href=\"Tailas\"&gt;Tailas&lt;/a&gt; turns the villagers against them. These warrens are the only way to reach the boat and return to the mainland.\nThe entrance to the warrens is a hidden door in a &lt;a href=\"Werewolf%20Village%20Huts%23AR2001\"&gt;hut&lt;/a&gt; in the Werewolf Village, just west of the &lt;a href=\"Werewolf%20Village%20Huts\"&gt;Chieftain's House&lt;/a&gt;. If Gorion's Ward helped &lt;a href=\"Dradeel\"&gt;Dradeel&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Maralee\"&gt;Maralee&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Delainy\"&gt;Delainy&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Durlyle\"&gt;Durlyle&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0earlier, these individuals will point them toward the entrance. Otherwise, the party must find it on their own, and will probably wander around the village fighting a lot more &lt;a href=\"Werewolf\"&gt;werewolves&lt;/a&gt; in the process.\nEncounters.\nAccording to dialogue, some of the werewolf villagers live in the warrens. It should come as no surprise, then, that the area is infested with werewolves.\nLoot.\nThere are several stashes of potions lying on the ground throughout the caverns. These are:"}
{"id": "2919", "revid": "5305940", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2919", "title": "Werewolf Island", "text": ""}
{"id": "15719", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15719", "title": "Werewolf Village Huts", "text": "The Werewolf Village, located on the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran%20South\"&gt;southern half&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Isle of Balduran&lt;/a&gt;, contains eleven huts which appear to serve as either common areas, sleeping areas or storage areas. Except for the Chieftain's House and Hut 1, the remaining nine do not serve much purpose in the overall arc of the adventure.\nOne convenient method of differentiating between these huts is referring to them by their internal &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area codes&lt;/a&gt; as defined by the game's developers. All eleven huts are listed below in sequential order by their area code. However, the game developers didn't always follow any type of definitive pattern specific to these huts when assigning area codes to them. The infobox to the right has an area image of the village that identifies every hut by its corresponding number in the infobox name.\nUnless otherwise specified, assume that NPCs carry nothing and all containers are unlocked.\nHut.\nThis is the biggest hut inside the walled compound of the village. It contains the hidden door that leads to the &lt;a href=\"Werewolf%20Caverns\"&gt;Werewolf Caverns&lt;/a&gt; and the ship that will get the party off the island and back to civilization. The hut is unpopulated and the only item of loot is a &lt;a href=\"dagger\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt; found on the table. The barrel is empty.\nChieftain's House.\nThe Chieftain's House is the medium-sized hut located in the center of the walled compound. It is here where &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party are directed to by the locals when they first reach the island. The headwoman &lt;a href=\"Kaishas%20Gan\"&gt;Kaishas Gan&lt;/a&gt; and another villager named &lt;a href=\"Tailas\"&gt;Tailas&lt;/a&gt; are found inside the hut. A search of the inside reveals the following loot: a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Heroism\"&gt;Potion of Heroism&lt;/a&gt; on the big table and a &lt;a href=\"Sunstone%20Gem\"&gt;Sunstone Gem&lt;/a&gt; inside the sack. The small table is empty.\nHut.\nThis hut is located across from the Chieftain's House inside the walled compound. The entrance is hidden from view, the hut is unpopulated, and the small table contains two &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potions of Healing&lt;/a&gt;. The big table and the sack are empty.\nHut.\nThis is the long, perpendicular hut located next to the Chieftain's House. Inside are five sleeping villagers who are present from 8:30 pm to 4:30 am. The table contains a &lt;a href=\"Jade%20Ring\"&gt;Jade Ring&lt;/a&gt; and the pillow is empty.\nHut.\nThis is the perpendicular hut located next to hut 3. The front door is hidden from view. It is populated by a villager from 7:30 am to 7:30 pm and by three sleeping villagers who are present from 8:30 pm to 4:30 am. The large barrel is empty and the pillow contains a &lt;a href=\"Chrysoberyl%20Gem\"&gt;Chrysoberyl Gem&lt;/a&gt;.\nHut.\nThis is the biggest of the three huts located on the small peninsula located to the south of the walled compound of the village. Storage huts 8 and 9 are located to the right of the hut. The inside is unpopulated and it contains three chests. The small chest on the floor contains three potions of healing. The big chest located near the middle of the hut contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Fire%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Fire Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Regeneration\"&gt;Potion of Regeneration&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"pearl\"&gt;pearl&lt;/a&gt;s. The chest on top of the table is empty.\nHut.\nThis is the hut located over the water. &lt;a href=\"Taloun\"&gt;Taloun&lt;/a&gt;, another shipwreck victim who wound up on the island, can be found inside. He'll provide some background on the villagers and their current plight.\nThe small chest on the floor contains two pearls. The big chest located near the middle of the hut contains a &lt;a href=\"Moonbar%20Gem\"&gt;Moonbar Gem&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"long%20sword\"&gt;long sword&lt;/a&gt;. The small chest on the table is empty.\nHut.\nThis is the middle hut located on the small peninsula between huts 6 and 9. The inside is populated by a male villager. The crate contains an &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Fiery%20Burning\"&gt;Oil of Fiery Burning&lt;/a&gt; potion and the shelf is empty.\nHut.\nThis is the small hut on the peninsula located next to hut 8. It is unpopulated. The shelf contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Explosions\"&gt;Potion of Explosions&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Murky%20Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Murky Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt; and the small table is empty.\nHut.\nThis is the hut located on the main part of the island, just to the north of huts 8 and 9. &lt;a href=\"Evalt\"&gt;Evalt&lt;/a&gt; can be found near the west side of the hut. Inside it is unpopulated and contains no loot.\nHut.\nThis is the other hut found on the main part of the island. It's located north of hut 7, near a grove of trees that are growing west of the walled compound. It's populated by a female villager. The chest contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Agility\"&gt;Potion of Agility&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Sphene%20Gem\"&gt;Sphene Gem&lt;/a&gt;. The crate is empty."}
