{"id": "43908", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43908", "title": "Werewyvern", "text": "A Werewyvern is a type of humanoid lycanthrope that can take the shape of a greater &lt;a href=\"Wyvern\"&gt;Wyvern&lt;/a&gt;. Only enchanted weapons can harm them, and they share traits of both the &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Wolfwere\"&gt;Greater Wolfwere&lt;/a&gt; and an adult &lt;a href=\"Wyvern\"&gt;Wyvern&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocations.\nThe only Werewyvern that appears in the game series appears in within &lt;a href=\"Abazigal%27s%20Lair%20Entrance%20Hall\"&gt;Abazigal's Lair Entrance Hall&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe creature is named as &lt;a href=\"Ekim%20Cyre\"&gt;Ekim Cyre&lt;/a&gt;, and first appears as a male human thief, who then transforms into a Werewyvern.\nEkrim is loyal to &lt;a href=\"Abazigal\"&gt;Abazigal&lt;/a&gt; and will fight to the death to destroy intruders in his master's lair-complex."}
{"id": "4306", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4306", "title": "West Baldur's Gate", "text": "West Baldur's Gate is one of nine districts of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate city&lt;/a&gt;. The inner wall of the city separates the area into two sections. Because of this, the southern section is only accessible from &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southwest&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, while the &lt;a href=\"%23Main%20section\"&gt;the main section of West Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; can only be visited from the other districts.\nSoutheast section.\n&lt;a href=\"Fenten\"&gt;Fenten&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Fenten%27s%20Home\"&gt;locked house&lt;/a&gt; on the left will refer the party to &lt;a href=\"Gerde\"&gt;Gerde&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Fishing%20Village\"&gt;Fishing Village&lt;/a&gt; in regards to &lt;a href=\"Ankheg\"&gt;Ankheg&lt;/a&gt;'s and buy &lt;a href=\"Ankheg%20Shell\"&gt;Ankheg Shell&lt;/a&gt;s for 250 each, or all the shells in your inventory for 250 (so drop/stash all but one shell every time you speak to him).\nIn the , &lt;a href=\"Taerom%20Fuiruim\"&gt;Taerom Fuiruim&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt; will buy individual shells for 500 apiece.\nReputation Trap.\nIf your Reputation is lower than 3 you will be attacked by a group of three &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23FLAMPUN\"&gt;Flaming Fist Enforcers&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Scout\"&gt;Flaming Fist Scout&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Battle%20Wizard\"&gt;Flaming Fist Battle Wizard&lt;/a&gt;. This group of soldiers will attack suddenly both on the streets and in the Hall of Wonders.\nTransitions.\nOnce the party has gone to transition between an area and any other area adjacent to it, even if they do not actually visit it, they can thenceforth travel to that area once on the transition map; it takes 0 hours. As with other World Map transitions, the direction the party was traveling from affects which side of the map they enter.\nCity map overview.\n City grid you are at the X:\n o|o|o &lt;a href=\"Northwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;NW&lt;/a&gt;|&lt;a href=\"North%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;|&lt;a href=\"Northeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;NE&lt;/a&gt; \n X|o|o W|&lt;a href=\"Central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;|&lt;a href=\"East%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;E&lt;/a&gt; \n o|o|o &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;SW&lt;/a&gt;|&lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;|&lt;a href=\"Southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;SE&lt;/a&gt;"}
