{"id": "3333", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3333", "title": "Whispers of Silence", "text": "Whispers of Silence, also known as Cloak of Non-Detection in and , is a cloak which offers protection from magical means to detect invisible creatures and objects, like the spell &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;, but for as long as the cloak is worn, which may come in handy for scouts of the party. It has a weight of 3 lbs. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, and and it will also appear in .\nWhere it is obtained from.\nIn Baldur's Gate, this cloak can be obtained from a &lt;a href=\"tasloi\"&gt;tasloi&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Lodge\"&gt;Cloakwood Lodge&lt;/a&gt; after &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Four\"&gt;Chapter Four&lt;/a&gt; begins.\nIn Baldur's Gate II, this cloak can be obtained from &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Amon\"&gt;Sorcerous Amon&lt;/a&gt; on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Den%20of%20the%20Seven%20Vales\"&gt;Den of the Seven Vales&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;, even from &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%201\"&gt;the first chapter&lt;/a&gt;. Either Amon and his fellow goons must be killed by the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;, or it must be pickpocketed from him.\nGameplay.\nUnlike the &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt; spell, the Non-Detection provided by this cloak is not of the type.\nAs this cloak has a differently coded Non-Detection effect than the spell, and as the cloak provides the user with an \"always on\" power, this means that the cloak has some benefits for certain player classes and item users.\nA player with the equipped &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20the%20Magi\"&gt;Staff of the Magi&lt;/a&gt; will remain invisible even if subjected to any invisibility removing spell effect, such as &lt;a href=\"Oracle\"&gt;Oracle&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"True%20Sight\"&gt;True Sight&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"True%20Seeing\"&gt;True Seeing&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe same benefit can be had from invisibility applied from the &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20of%20the%20Star\"&gt;Dagger of the Star&lt;/a&gt;.\nA player who has the ability to become hidden through &lt;a href=\"Stealth\"&gt;Stealth&lt;/a&gt;, such as a rogue, &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Bounty%20Hunter\"&gt;Bounty Hunter&lt;/a&gt; will gain additional protection with this cloak equipped. These classes/kits who are successfully hidden will resist being exposed from spell casting opponents using spells such as Oracle and True sight.\nThis cloak is superior in every way to the spell version of Non-Detection.\nIt does not protect against enemies who can innately &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;."}
