{"id": "17999", "revid": "53032777", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17999", "title": "Wild Forest", "text": "Wild Forest is accessible in \"Shadows of Amn\" campaign of from &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;. It is the recruitment location for &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt; and the location of her companion quest &lt;a href=\"Neera%27s%20Hidden%20Refuge\"&gt;Neera's Hidden Refuge&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay (Walk-through).\nAccording to Neera, who seeks to join the party and go with you to the &lt;a href=\"Hidden%20Refuge\"&gt;Hidden Refuge&lt;/a&gt;, there are numerous traps throughout the area. \nA gnome called &lt;a href=\"Quaid\"&gt;Quaid&lt;/a&gt; stands by a broken cart. You could speak with him and see if he needs help mending it. He may know of hidden dangers in the Wild Forest, or the path to follow to get to the &lt;a href=\"Hidden%20Refuge\"&gt;Hidden Refuge&lt;/a&gt;.\nA Speaking Snake, of all things can be encountered. If you talk to it, the snake says -\"\"Death Awaitsss,(CHARNAME RACE)! Death awaits, and I show the way!\". More chatter and warnings will continue, and promises of Death awaiting if you pass the snake. The beast never turns hostile but will move at rapid speed towards anyone who may attack it. Is this some kind of trick or illusion? A Wild Mage's Hidden Forest defense?\nA small group of Hobgoblins will attack the party if you are observed. Their corpses may provide some treasure.\nTwo Gnoll Elites and a Captain can be found, as well as a monstrous Ettin that seems to be hunting them.\nSeveral wild beasts including great cats, spiders and Wyverns roam the area, and they will attack on sight.\nDepending on the path you take, you could come upon a pair of hostile Ogres. If you approach or engage the creatures, there is a possible surprise from an invisible Ogre Mage.\nA cluster of ten kobolds may be seen, and they will attack if you are observed.\nIn the northeast side of the Wild Forest is seen a destroyed bridge that used to span the churning waters of the stream. As you near it, a text display reads \"This bridge appears rotten and uncrossable. The water flowing beneath is polluted with magic. It has an unwholesome and eerie look that is distinctly unwelcoming\"\". If &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt; is in your party, she will help out with the situation, as long as she is close enough to the broken structure to examine it. If so, there will be a 2000 experience point reward for each party member, and she will solve the issue (which she actually created earlier as part of the defenses for the Hidden Refuge). Otherwise, find a \"A Pile of Gravel\" which may help as well."}
{"id": "4640", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4640", "title": "Wild Mage", "text": "This page is for the wild mage &lt;a href=\"Classes\"&gt;class kit&lt;/a&gt;, available in &lt;a href=\"Enhanced%20Edition\"&gt;Enhanced Edition&lt;/a&gt;s and in the original if has been installed.\nIntroduction.\nWild Mages are &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;s trained in use of wild magic. Whenever they cast a memorized spell, there is 5% chance (casting\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Nahal%27s%20Reckless%20Dweomer\"&gt;Nahal's Reckless Dweomer&lt;/a&gt; pushes the chance to 100%) of a &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Surge\"&gt;Wild Surge&lt;/a&gt;, which can have beneficial or detrimental side effects. Wild Mages also have a -5 to +5 adjust range to their levels every time they cast a spell. The growth of most spells caps at level 20, but higher caster level does make them harder to &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;dispel&lt;/a&gt;.\nLike &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;Specialist Mage&lt;/a&gt;s, they depend on spells in battles, learn magic from scrolls, and cast spells from a wizard spellbook. Wild Mages receive 1 additional spell in every spell level, but unlike Specialists, they do not have an opposing spell school and can cast spells from all 8 schools of magic.\nIn order for mages to cast a spell, first they need to successfully scribe a mage spell scroll into their spell book (scroll lost in process regardless of success or failure), in which they must prepare the spell by putting it into an empty spell slot, then they have to rest to get the spell ready.\nOnly &lt;a href=\"Humans\"&gt;Humans&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Elves\"&gt;Elves&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Half-elf\"&gt;Half-Elves&lt;/a&gt; may become Wild Mages. Wild mages cannot &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Dual-class\"&gt;dual class&lt;/a&gt;.\nAbility scores table.\nFor the information of this table, the human race was used, because humans don't have any bonuses to the primary abilities and act as a 'neutral'. For all other races, these numbers might be slightly different.\nWild Mage Spellbook.\nWild Mages are able to cast spells from the &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20spells%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Wizard Spellbook&lt;/a&gt; and learn spells from scrolls. They start with 3 additional spells related to wild magic: &lt;a href=\"Nahal%27s%20Reckless%20Dweomer\"&gt;Nahal's Reckless Dweomer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Shield\"&gt;Chaos Shield&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Chaos%20Shield\"&gt;Improved Chaos Shield&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0\u00a0\n&lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class abilities&lt;/a&gt;.\nMages can access to level 10 spells, which are added to the level 9 wizard spellbook after they have been chosen. These spells are:\nCaster level modification.\nWhen a Wild Mage casts a spell, their caster level may be increased or lowered by a random amount. The combat log will display a message such as \"\" when that happens.\nEach spell is affected in its own way by the caster level, but typically duration of effects scale upwards, and it isn't rare that damage does too. Scaling almost always caps at level 20, and it doesn't necessarily increase smoothly \u2013 &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Arrow\"&gt;Flame Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, for example, doesn't grow at all until it suddenly gains a whole new arrow with full damage at levels 10, 15 and 20. Quite a few spells only scale starting from a certain level, like &lt;a href=\"Abi-Dalzim%27s%20Horrid%20Wilting\"&gt;Abi-Dalzim's Horrid Wilting&lt;/a&gt;: Since it scales from level 16 to 20, even if a level 16 Wild Mage gets a -5 modifier when trying to cast it, the damage dealt will be 16d8, not 11d8. And with a +5 modifier, the damage will be 20d8, not 21d8.\nFinally, the modifier is tame at low levels, such that a level 1 Wild Mage would not be able to cast a &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt; with 3 projectiles \u2013 a feat only available to mages level 5 and above. See below each possible value that the caster level modifier can take, along with its associated odds.\nKit recommended items.\nThese are usable by &lt;a href=\"Mages\"&gt;Mages&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sorcerers\"&gt;Sorcerers&lt;/a&gt; (so are not kit exclusive equipments), but are highly recommended for Wild Mages, while nearly useless for other wizards.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"The%20Tweaks%20Anthology\"&gt;Tweaks Anthology mod&lt;/a&gt; allows human Wild Mages to dual class."}
{"id": "53540", "revid": "53755656", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53540", "title": "Wild Shape (BG3)", "text": "Wild Shape is a &lt;a href=\"Druid%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt; spell in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20III\"&gt;Baldur's Gate III&lt;/a&gt;. It is learned at Druid level 2.\nDescription.\n\"Magically assume the shape of a beast. While in animal shape, you can't talk or cast Spells.\""}
