{"id": "12538", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12538", "title": "Wilson", "text": "Wilson is a true neutral &lt;a href=\"Brown%20Bear\"&gt;grizzly bear&lt;/a&gt; and a potential &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; in and .\nRecruitment.\nWilson\u00a0is available to recruit from &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;. Speak to &lt;a href=\"Zaviak\"&gt;Zaviak&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Hidden%20Refuge\"&gt;Hidden Refuge&lt;/a&gt; and agree to find Wilson for him, you'll encounter the bear during &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%20yn%20Bashir\"&gt;Rasaad&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"https%3A//baldursgate.wikia.com/wiki/Rasaad%2527s_Journey\"&gt;companion quest&lt;/a&gt; near the entrance of the &lt;a href=\"Heretic%20Temple\"&gt;Heretic Temple&lt;/a&gt;. After talking to the bear, you may free him either by purchasing him for or killing his captor &lt;a href=\"Jolstead\"&gt;Jolstead&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0Wilson\u00a0will then wait for\u00a0you at starting zone of this area, where you can invite him to join the party.\nHe'll become unavailable if you advance too far in &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt;'s or &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%20yn%20Bashir\"&gt;Rasaad&lt;/a&gt;'s companion quests line.\nGameplay.\nHis powers increase with levels:\nHe is considered to be dual-wielding weapons and he has master proficiency in the two-weapon style (3 pips). His claws are his main hand weapon and deal 1d6+2 slashing damage, with a 15% chance to Hug an enemy for an extra 2d6 crushing damage every hit. His bites are his off-hand weapon, dealing 1d10+2 piercing damage. Both have a speed factor of 3.\nMay use &lt;a href=\"Animal%20Rage\"&gt;Animal Rage&lt;/a&gt; ablity (-2 bonus to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, +2 damage, immunity to charm, fear, confusion, hold, stun, sleep, and &lt;a href=\"Feeblemind\"&gt;Feeblemind&lt;/a&gt; for 1 turn) once every 6 levels.\nCan drink healing potions and antidotes but nothing else. Cannot wear anything. Cannot initiate conversations manually.\nPersonality.\nWilson speaks in growls and snorts, which only &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and Zaviak seem to be able to understand. Judging by how they treat him, he is a remarkably gentle, 'well-spoken' and cheerful grizzly."}
{"id": "48846", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48846", "title": "Windspear Cabin", "text": "The Windspear Cabin is the home of the paladin &lt;a href=\"Garren%20Windspear\"&gt;Garren Windspear&lt;/a&gt; and it is located in the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; area. The cabin's only function is a meeting place of sorts to interact with Garren. The cabin's four containers have no treasure."}
{"id": "7341", "revid": "1966519", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7341", "title": "Windspear Hills", "text": "Windspear Hills is an area in the \"Shadows of Amn\" campaign that becomes accessible either by accepting a quest from the dryads on the first level of &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon%201st%20Floor\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon&lt;/a&gt; or from &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Jierdan\"&gt;Lord Jierdan&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;.\nConfronting Monsters.\nUpon arrival you\u2019re attacked by a group of elegantly speaking monsters. If you have &lt;a href=\"Keldorn\"&gt;Keldorn&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Anomen\"&gt;Anomen&lt;/a&gt; in the party, after the battle they\u2019ll identify one of the dead monsters as the paladin &lt;a href=\"Ajantis%20Ilvastarr\"&gt;Ajantis&lt;/a&gt;, one of your former companions who, along with his squire and several other knights, were under an illusion that made them all appear as monsters. Obviously somebody is plotting to frame you by arousing the anger of the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf you accept &lt;a href=\"Garren%20Windspear\"&gt;Garren Windspear&lt;/a&gt;\u2019s hospitality and follow him to his &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Cabin\"&gt;cabin&lt;/a&gt;, he\u2019ll provide you shelter and set off to try to clear your name by contacting some of his former influences within the Order.\nIf you choose not to kill the monsters, then the cabin will be empty, and the entrance to the northeastern &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;dungeon&lt;/a&gt; will be blocked.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"CoM%20Encounters\"&gt;CoM Encounters&lt;/a&gt; mod adds several additional encounters in various places of . One of these occurs adjacent to the \"Dungeon Entrance\" location on the Windspear Hills map. This encounter is a group of veteran mercenaries hired by \"Mr. F\" to hinder &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;. They'll not let your party enter without going through them first. Some unique loot is possible if you are able to defeat these warriors."}
