{"id": "5963", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5963", "title": "Bring the Poisoned Man to his Friends", "text": "Bring the Poisoned Man to his Friends is a &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; during the in campaign.\nAcquisition.\nIn a random encounter between areas, you will come across a band of &lt;a href=\"Thug%20%28Random%29\"&gt;Thugs&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Mage%20%28Random%29\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt; attacking a man. The thugs will turn on you and you must defeat them. After they are all dead, the man will cry out for help. He will explain that he has been poisoned and will die unless he is immediately taken to his friends. The poison is such that regular spells and antidotes will not cure him. The player's journal will then be updated with this quest.\nWalkthrough.\nThe poisoned man's name is &lt;a href=\"Renfeld\"&gt;Renfeld&lt;/a&gt;. He will implore you to bring him to his colleague in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt; to the building in the southwest called the &lt;a href=\"Galvarey%20Estate\"&gt;Galvarey Estate&lt;/a&gt;.\nWarning: If the character who is speaking to Renfeld during the automatic conversation after the fight has no inventory slots open, if his quest is accepted, he will be automatically dropped on the ground, at which point he will explode (as if killed by a massive hit) and cease to be an item. The quest is not updated if this happens, but the lack of a living or dead body will prevent the quest from continuing.\nBring &lt;a href=\"Renfeld%27s%20Body\"&gt;Renfeld's Body&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Rylock\"&gt;Rylock&lt;/a&gt; at the front door of the estate.\nRewards depending upon actions and dialog range anywhere from 0 up to and 0 to for the party.\nOutcomes.\nThis quest is prerequisite in order to &lt;a href=\"Find%20out%20What%20Happened%20to%20Montaron\"&gt;Find out What Happened to Montaron&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Xzar\"&gt;Xzar&lt;/a&gt; will appear near the stairs to the &lt;a href=\"Sea%27s%20Bounty%20Tavern\"&gt;Sea's Bounty Tavern&lt;/a&gt; to enlist the party's aid.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mods improve and raises the challenge factor of the encounter with Renfeld's kidnappers - that takes place in Athkatla (when travelling between areas) in Chapter 2. The enemy group is composed of a Mage, Cleric, one or two thieves and a fighter class thug. All of the creatures will use smarter scripts that allow some prepared buffs for the mage and cleric, and potion of invisibility use by the thief (for backstabbing), as well as healing potion use if the creature is damaged over a certain percentage. This is much more difficult than the unmodified game, but especially for a low-level beginning party."}
{"id": "7873", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7873", "title": "Britik", "text": "Britik is a unique &lt;a href=\"chaotic%20neutral\"&gt;chaotic neutral&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=\"chaotic%20evil\"&gt;chaotic evil&lt;/a&gt; gnoll chieftain in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". He is likely the strongest of the gnolls in the &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Camp\"&gt;Bandit Camp&lt;/a&gt;, a good reason he may be found among three other mercenaries - &lt;a href=\"Venkt\"&gt;Venkt&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Raemon\"&gt;Raemon&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Hakt\"&gt;Hakt&lt;/a&gt; - within &lt;a href=\"Tazok\"&gt;Tazok&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Tazok%27s%20Tent\"&gt;Tazok's Tent&lt;/a&gt;, guarding the captured spy &lt;a href=\"Ender%20Sai\"&gt;Ender Sai&lt;/a&gt; and ready for a fight."}
{"id": "20994", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20994", "title": "Broken Armor", "text": "Broken Armor is an item from unimplemented mechanic of metal armors getting destroyed during &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Crisis\"&gt;Iron Crisis&lt;/a&gt;, similar to how destroyed iron weapons end up being &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Weapon\"&gt;Broken Weapon&lt;/a&gt;s.\nFrom what can be found in game files, it was supposed to work on a same way as the mechanic behind weapon breaking, replacing a regular items with their broken equivalent. With initially rather high price of metal armors in-game, the lack of this mechanic certainly eases things up."}
