{"id": "3778", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3778", "title": "Broken Weapon", "text": "In Baldur's Gate (and its Enhanced Edition), every unenchanted iron or steel melee weapon (including those involved in sidequests, such as &lt;a href=\"Perdue%27s%20Short%20Sword\"&gt;Perdue's Short Sword&lt;/a&gt;, but excluding &lt;a href=\"Katana\"&gt;Katanas&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Wakizashi\"&gt;Wakizashis&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ninjat%C5%8D\"&gt;Ninjat\u014ds&lt;/a&gt; in the EE) has a 1% chance on-hit to break due to the iron crisis, good quality iron and steel are scarce, weapons will break easier. The fragmented weapon can't be reforged, recycled or sold and serves no purpose.\u00a0This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and ."}
