{"id": "8389", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8389", "title": "Brother Pol", "text": "Brother Pol is a cleric mage of &lt;a href=\"Helm\"&gt;Helm&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Knights%20of%20the%20Vigil\"&gt;Knight of the Vigil&lt;/a&gt;. He's found in a group of knights at the foot of &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. He is one of the six knights seen positioned in front of the grand covered staircase leading to the Keep's roof. \nGameplay.\nWhen you arrive at Watcher's Keep, &lt;a href=\"Odren\"&gt;Odren&lt;/a&gt; the leader of the group will be waiting below the looming structure. The player must initiate dialogue. Once dialogue is underway, at some point he'll ask you to perform a ritual to fortify the seals that hold the Imprisoned One beneath the keep. If the party agrees, the knights will then escort you to the top of the fortress (in a cutscene move).\nBrother Pol will have some interjections during the parlay with Odren and the Knights.\nOdren explains that: \nWhen ready, speak with Brother Pol and ask questions and explore all the dialogue options available. This gives some background information about the history, purpose and recent troubles encountered in Watcher's Keep.\nBrother Pol will eventually say:\nHe continues:\nThe party will receive the &lt;a href=\"Vigil%20Stone\"&gt;Vigil Stone&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Ritual%20Scroll\"&gt;Ritual Scroll&lt;/a&gt;. With these items in hand, the Altar level of the Keep can be entered and exited by the rooftop transition point in the special metallic hemisphere when desired.\nIf the party ends up in combat with the knights, including Brother Pol, he'll have access to only arcane magic, as outlined in the InfoBox's scripted spell use.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to Brother Pol. \nHe is provided with a randomly assigned Mage kit (on mod installation) and could be a Conjurer, Enchanter, Invoker or Necromancer. The kit selection will determine the spell book assigned to the mage. Regardless of what kit is assigned, expect a more robust opening chain of buffs to protect the creature.\nIn addition to a revised spell book of arcane magic, since Brother Pol is &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20/%20Mage\"&gt;Cleric / Mage&lt;/a&gt; he also will have a repertoire of divine magic scripted for use.\nSCS really piles on the initial protective buffs when there are multiclass spell casters. Brother Pol will have a mixture of arcane and divine magic buffs at the outset of hostilities. He's going to require some work to remove his defenses. A single Breach spell isn't going to do it.\nA prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; can be instantly deployed as well.\nA ready to use potion is scripted for use to heal damage or enhance abilities.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod is installed, those spells will be the SR versions."}
{"id": "15895", "revid": "53755656", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15895", "title": "Brown Bear", "text": "Brown Bears are common creatures, often found roaming the wilderness. They typically travel alone, though they can be found in pairs. They are non-hostile passive animals that like to wander, but will turn hostile if one were to get too close. They drop no items when killed."}
{"id": "56248", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56248", "title": "Brown Dragon Acid Breath", "text": "Brown Dragon Acid Breath is an innate ability available to Brown Dragons in the game saga. \nThis innate ability is initiated via internal creature scripting during combat. The purpose of the spell is to apply &lt;a href=\"Acid%20damage\"&gt;Acid damage&lt;/a&gt; in an Area of Effect to the dragon's enemies.\nEffects.\nThe ability is uninterruptible and takes little time to deploy. The scripted targeting will fire over a selected target and area surrounding it.\nThis is typically within the creature's sight detection range. \nAll creatures in the area of effect are subject to the effects. Rather than a cone of acid spreading forth from the dragon, this projectile will burst from the central aiming point/target and spread in a ring of corrosive destruction. \nWhen a dragon deploys an acid dragon breath, a blast explodes upon enemies within the AoE who are then subjected to 24d6 &lt;a href=\"Acid%20damage\"&gt;Acid damage&lt;/a&gt;. A quick reaction &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs Breath will apply, and a successful save will reduce the damage by half. Perhaps the victim was able to dive aside, roll away from the burst, or raise a shield up to deflect some of the spray. \nGameplay.\nAny form of acid protection and or acid damage resistance will help mitigate the powerful blast. \nNo magic resistance or spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; can stop the dragon acid, except for a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Shield\"&gt;Spell Shield&lt;/a&gt; - which is bugged and isn't consumed after the attack. \nAs this acid blast ability has an area of effect, a &lt;a href=\"Reflected%20Image\"&gt;Reflected Image&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; illusion won't interact with the spell and offers no protection/decoy capability.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mods reclassify Dragon Breath attacks as having no Spell School or \"Secondary Type\". \nThis breath weapon is not a \"Magic Attack\" type, but a \"None\" classification. This means that certain spells or items that protect against this secondary type will be bypassed, such as a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Shield\"&gt;Spell Shield&lt;/a&gt;."}
