{"id": "54143", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54143", "title": "Bruenor", "text": "Bruenor, whose surname is \"Battlehammer\", is a companion with &lt;a href=\"Drizzt%20Do%27Urden\"&gt;Drizzt Do'Urden&lt;/a&gt;. The group can be encountered only in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt;. This can first occur after the player's party exits the &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Temple%20at%20Underdark%20Exit\"&gt;Elven Temple at Underdark Exit&lt;/a&gt; area and selects another destination from the &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nBruenor's first appearance is covered in the &lt;a href=\"Encounter%20-%20Drizzt%20Do%27Urden\"&gt;Encounter - Drizzt Do'Urden&lt;/a&gt; page.\nHis second potential appearance is outlined in &lt;a href=\"The%20final%20battle%20with%20Bodhi\"&gt;The final battle with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; page. If he is killed in the first encounter, then the second encounter is moot.\nIf the party is engaged in combat with Bruenor (this can happen in the Chapter 6 encounter with Drizzt), he behaves as a melee attacking fighter. He'll close to melee range to the nearest detected target, and slash with abandon with his enchanted axe.\nThe combat script will often have him apply an &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt;. He can also consume the &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Extra%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Extra Healing&lt;/a&gt; when HP falls to 50% of original.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod changes the AI scripting used by Bruenor, to improve tactical behavior and item usage.\nSCS adds 2 pips in sword and shield fighting style to the dwarf.\nAn additional potion is added to Bruenor for use."}
{"id": "7745", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7745", "title": "Brun", "text": "Brun is a farmer whose can be found standing in front of his &lt;a href=\"Farmer%20Brun%27s%20Home\"&gt;house&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Fishing%20Village\"&gt;Fishing Village&lt;/a&gt; area. His &lt;a href=\"Farmer%20Brun%27s%20Missing%20Son\"&gt;son is missing&lt;/a&gt;, he's just about destitute, and he could really use some help. \nFarmer &lt;a href=\"Brun%27s%20Dead%20Son\"&gt;Brun's son&lt;/a&gt; can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Ankheg%20Pit\"&gt;Ankheg Pit&lt;/a&gt; located west of the farm. You will find his body in a large hoard of treasure located near the rear of the underground warrens.\nAfter delivering his dead son to him for a 500XP reward, talk to him again and give him () and a &lt;a href=\"Ruby%20Ring\"&gt;ruby ring&lt;/a&gt; (found on one of the ankhegs in the pit) for an extra 1100 XP and +1 &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt; or just for an extra 1000 XP and +1 Reputation."}
