{"id": "50533", "revid": "284618", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50533", "title": "Brunson", "text": "Brunson is a so called \"squatter\" gathered in Imnesvale, along with &lt;a href=\"Pardo\"&gt;Pardo&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Moreno\"&gt;Moreno&lt;/a&gt;. This is part of the &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20Stronghold%20Duties\"&gt;Paladin Stronghold Duties&lt;/a&gt;. All three are assembled outside the &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Baron%20Metrich\"&gt;Baron Metrich&lt;/a&gt; does not want you to speak with these individuals and has labelled them as illegal 'squatters\" on his land and wants them removed. If you do speak with Brunson, then you will gain additional information, that could very well refute what the Baron has stated. "}
{"id": "35799", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35799", "title": "Brus", "text": "Brus is &lt;a href=\"Gaelan%20Bayle\"&gt;Gaelan Bayle&lt;/a&gt;'s nephew and serves as a messenger for his uncle in &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thief&lt;/a&gt; affairs and plays a role in the \"\" &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;main quest&lt;/a&gt;.\nInvolvement.\nBrus can be found outside Gaelan's house once &lt;a href=\"Collect%20the%20fee%20for%20Gaelan%20Bayle\"&gt;Collect the fee for Gaelan Bayle&lt;/a&gt; has begun. He will offer tips on how to obtain the fee, directing towards the .\nBrus appears a second time once Gorion's Ward has &lt;a href=\"Meeting%20with%20Valen%27s%20mistress\"&gt;met Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; and discussed the trip to &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt; with her. He will claim that Gaelan has a counteroffer to make and urge the party to meet his uncle one more time. Gaelan will then lower his price from 20,000 to 15,000 &lt;a href=\"Gold%20Piece\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nMods.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Loron%27s%20Return%20%28Ajoc%27s%20minimod%20restored%29\"&gt;Loron's Return (Ajoc's minimod restored)&lt;/a&gt; mod uses Brus to start off this mod. Brus will deliver a message to the party, inviting you to initiate the questline (or not)."}
{"id": "6135", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6135", "title": "Brynnlaw", "text": "Brynnlaw is a sandy island located amidst the &lt;a href=\"Sea%20of%20Swords\"&gt;Sea of Swords&lt;/a&gt; just off the coast of &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt;. At some point in its history, Brynnlaw was taken over by pirates and quickly became a pirate town. &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;, a mysterious \"asylum\", is located on the north side of the island, and is ostensibly operated by the &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizards\"&gt;Cowled Wizards&lt;/a&gt; order.\nDescription.\nOnce a small sea trading town offering a port haven from storms and a stop for fishermen, sea merchants to restock provisions, crew rest and some basic services - the town has since been forcefully taken over by pirates. The local townsfolk have been upended, some murdered, and displaced by the rule of the Pirate Lord. The town has some kind of relationship with the Spellhold asylum, and they coexist with an unknown arrangement. Brynnlaw is outside the sphere of influence of Amn or any other kingdom, and is currently just an outlaw island, and a temporary stop over for various independent traders, pirates, and daring mercantile sea farers. \nThe town is home to a small population of dockhands and some fishermen, but the majority are pirates and transient visitors. The town maintains a working dock, moorage for anchored ships, a general store/shop, Inn, Temple and a Brothel. A grand home has been confiscated by the Pirate Lord as his residence and headquarters. The Northern side of the island is occupied by the strange and mysterious structure of Spellhold, the Asylum. \nGameplay.\nUpon arrival to Brynnlaw, depending on if the party sided with the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; or if on &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;'s side will determine a certain encounter for the party.\nIf the party is on the Shadow Thieves' side, then the party will arrive at night, and &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sime\"&gt;Sime&lt;/a&gt; will have certain dialogue. Afterwards the party will learn that a betrayal is afoot, and that a trio of &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; assailants are waiting to ambush your group. A battle with &lt;a href=\"Del\"&gt;Del&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Parisa\"&gt;Parisa&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Valen\"&gt;Valen&lt;/a&gt; will take place. If you are successful in driving away the undead attackers, Sime will let you know to visit Brynnlaw's Inn, the Vulgar Monkey, she'll say \"\"Go to the tavern. Speak with a man named Sanik. If there is a way into the asylum, he will know it\".\" - and soon after she will tell you \"I will scout around a bit and meet you at the pass leading to the asylum itself. Work with haste, &lt;CHARNAME&gt;. Our enemies know we are here.\" \nUpon arrival to the island having sided with Bodhi, then Saemon will have dialogue with the party, with several statements and questions answered. In the end he'll say \"H\"erein you shall find what you need. I will go no further lest I be recognized and harm your efforts. The Vulgar Monkey tavern should hold what you are looking for.\" And perhaps soon afterwards say \"Speak with Sanik inside. He has little love for me, but there is scant about this town that does not pass his notice.\"\"\nAs the party moves about Brynnlaw while exploring the streets, there will be some opportunities to speak with various folks. Dockhands and fishermen will have a bit to say and fill-in the town's mood. \nThe first time the party approaches the Brothel entrance, a duel of some kind is about to take place, involving a so called \"Duel Coordinator\", and two foes named Adante and Dirbish the Black. After their randomly resolved fight, there will be a parting line or two. And as is normal for BG games, the party can just walk over to the corpse and loot the body, while a few onlookers watch the pilfering. Perfectly normal behavior, especially for a Pirate town like Brynnlaw.\nIf you wish, speak with some of the Courtesans in front of the Brothel. The party can get some info from these physically attractive workers. There are male and female choices available. \nAs the party wanders around, perhaps dispelling the \"Fog of War\", it is likely that an encounter with a pair of pirates will be seen - squaring off in a fight - they are named Andar and Olben. They don't have any dialogue, except for some \"Argh's\" and other pirate-like exclamations as they circle each other. If you wish to get involved, send them to Davey Jones locker in speedier fashion, and attack the Pirates. They will become hostile if attacked, but otherwise they may eventually fight amongst themselves on their own. They drop a few items when slashed and stabbed sufficiently.\nAt some point, a small boy will perform a pick pocketing on &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;. This encounter with &lt;a href=\"Ason\"&gt;Ason&lt;/a&gt; is covered as part of the quest. Also, the party can speak with &lt;a href=\"Ginia\"&gt;Ginia&lt;/a&gt; on the eastern side of the town. Both these characters are related to the optional quest.\nAt various times, and typically after sundown, the streets of Brynnlaw can present some dangers. There are spawning points on the map that are scripted to generate backstabbing thief pirates. These scoundrels will be invisible and just attack with little warning, although the player may see some text in the screen log where the attacker says some kind of threat.\nThere is also one larger spawn involving a whole group of pirates and thieves that will challenge the party - it's some kind of press gang that is attempting to capture the party to force them into a Pirate Ship crew servitude. This naturally leads to a fight on dockside area of Brynnlaw, and is basically unavoidable. This encounter does not trigger until after returning to Brynnlaw from &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;, and only during the late evening and nighttime.\nContainers.\nThroughout the main Brynnlaw townscape are various barrels, crates and miscellaneous cargo containers with nothing in them, or random treasures or even a &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Paralyzation\"&gt;Wand of Paralyzation&lt;/a&gt; in a secret wall niche. These are all for the taking if the party finds them. \nMod content.\nMod screenshots.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Back%20to%20Brynnlaw\"&gt;Back to Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt; mod begins in Athkatla in Chapter 6 and is initiated by speaking with a figure near the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer%20Mart\"&gt;Adventurer Mart&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;. If pursued, the party will be returning to Brynnlaw again for new content and quest adventures.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20for%20BG2\"&gt;Unfinished Business for BG2&lt;/a&gt; mod restores the character Greyhand to the game, who is encountered at the north part of Brynnlaw on the pathway to the Spellhold map transition. Greyhand will drop the deprecated \"Boots of Hastened Departure\" as shown in &lt;a href=\"https%3A//imgur.com/9524z9x\"&gt;this screenshot&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Pack\"&gt;Quest Pack&lt;/a&gt; mod finishes an earlier quest in the Vulgar Monkey Inn. See that page for details.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sime%20%28mod%29\"&gt;Sime (mod)&lt;/a&gt; companion modification, if installed, will begin here in Brynnlaw. \nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes minor revisions to pirates and thieves in Brynnlaw, as well as various guards in the Brothel. These changes are the usual creature class AI scripting modifications to allow for smarter tactical behavior, item use (such as potions carried), and corrected weapon proficiencies and fighting styles commensurate with the class and level of the creature. Of particular note, Pirate Thieves encountered at night will attack from invisibility, attempt to &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt;. and if they have a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invisibility\"&gt;Potion of Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; in their inventory, use that, and attempt another backstabbing, if able. Special care must be taken to prevent \"squishy\" party members from being \"chunked\" from excessive damage."}
{"id": "6159", "revid": "282322", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6159", "title": "Brynnlaw Store", "text": "The Brynnlaw Store\" \"is a small shop found on the island of &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThis well kept building houses the Brynnlaw Store. The publicly accessible portion of the shop is in one large room, packed with tables, shelving, some sea chests, a stove and a small foundry. Several arms racks display weapons. A number of battle tested and decorative shields hang on the walls. Some armor hauberks and similar mail is folded and stowed for sale as well. If the nimble-fingered party should dare, then some bastard swords, spears and even a &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt; can be found within, free of charge. \nGameplay.\nAn unnamed \"Storekeep\" mans this place of trade. He's impatient, and somewhat rude. If you are caught stealing from him then you'll have a 2-point reputation loss, each time the larceny is detected. He's also classified as an innocent, so if killed the party can add on a huge reputation penalty from that as well."}
