{"id": "2396", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2396", "title": "Bub Snikt", "text": "Bub Snikt is a hunter encountered in the &lt;a href=\"South%20Beregost%20Road\"&gt;Area South of Beregost&lt;/a&gt;. He's found just to the northwest of the &lt;a href=\"Beregost%20Cave\"&gt;cave&lt;/a&gt; entrance.\nHe'll immediately attempt conversation with the first party member who enters his line of sight. He tells you that he's hunting &lt;a href=\"ogre\"&gt;ogre&lt;/a&gt;s, and that he can smell two nearby. He also tells you that he works alone, and will not join the party. He can be killed at no penalty.\nDialogue.\n\"Keep low and quiet! Can you smell it? Ogres on the breeze. Two, maybe more.\"\nTrivia.\nWolverine references.\nMarvel fans will notice the various references this character makes to the super hero Wolverine."}
{"id": "48300", "revid": "281116", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48300", "title": "Bubbles", "text": "Bubbles is a female human who is the love interest of both &lt;a href=\"Carbos\"&gt;Carbos&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shank\"&gt;Shank&lt;/a&gt;, two individuals who were presumed to have been killed by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. All three of them are found near the left side of the &lt;a href=\"Estate%20of%20Saerk%20Farrahd\"&gt;Estate of Saerk Farrahd&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;. The two boys end up coming to blows over the young lass, with the winner having lost the girl in the end anyway.\nDialogue.\n\"You shall never have her, you ridiculous fool!\" (Carbos)\n\"No! She loves ME. ME!\" (Carbos)\n\"\"Fight over her? What an excellent idea! Yes, we shall fight over our beloved Bubbles!\"' (Carbos)\n\"Certainly, if you wish to.\" (Carbos)\nFighting commences.\n\"Aha! That moron, Shank, is now dead! I am victorious! Come, my Bubbles... let us go and celebrate this blessed event!\"\n\"Bubbles? But... but Bubbles?! Honey melon, where are you going?\"\n\"Most excellent! I have defeated the loathsome Carbos! Come, my beloved Bubbles... let us go!\"\n\"Bubbles! But... but Bubbles! But I love you, my chicken pot pie! Come back!\""}
{"id": "4059", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4059", "title": "Buckler", "text": "Bucklers \u2014 so called because they can be \"buckled\" to the forearm \u2014 are the smallest shields available, usually made from wood or metal. They can be use by many classes, except &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Kensai\"&gt;Kensai&lt;/a&gt;. These shields are available in three different styles, like the larger-sized shields, and in six styles in &lt;a href=\"Enhanced%20Edition\"&gt;Enhanced Edition&lt;/a&gt;s.\nLike all standard shields, bucklers offer an armor class bonus of +1. However, because of their marginal size provides, they provide no protection against missile and piercing weapons. So to further clarify, a buckler provides an armor class bonus vs. Slashing and crushing melee attacks, but not piercing or missile attacks. Despite the \"no protection from piercing or missile' attacks\", your overall Armor Class rating number display on the Character screen will show a +1 bonus to AC when the buckler is equipped.\nLocations.\n\"Tales of the Sword Coast\".\nTreasure.\nOn a trapped shelf in &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20One%29\"&gt;Durlag's Tower (Labyrinth Level One)&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "36211", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36211", "title": "Buckler +1", "text": "The Buckler +1 is a magically enhanced version of the &lt;a href=\"Buckler\"&gt;Buckler&lt;/a&gt;. Like the base item, it does not provide defense against &lt;a href=\"Missile%20damage\"&gt;missile&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;piercing&lt;/a&gt; attacks.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;Companions&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Glint%20Gardnersonson\"&gt;Glint Gardnersonson&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Voghiln\"&gt;Voghiln&lt;/a&gt; have versions of this item as their starting equipment.\nBuckler +1 can be found at various locations and for sale throughout the realm, including from &lt;a href=\"Belegarm\"&gt;Belegarm&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Brendak\"&gt;Brendak&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hue%20Greenleaf\"&gt;Hue Greenleaf&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Jegg\"&gt;Jegg&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Waizahb\"&gt;Waizahb&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s can carry a similar item, the &lt;a href=\"Buckler%20%2B1%20%28Skeleton%20shield%29\"&gt;Buckler +1 (Skeleton shield)&lt;/a&gt;, which cannot be dropped."}
