{"id": "8219", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8219", "title": "Buckley's Buckler", "text": "Buckley's Buckler is an enchanted\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Buckler\"&gt;Buckler&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0sold at\u00a0&lt;a href=\"The%20Friendly%20Arm\"&gt;The Friendly Arm&lt;/a&gt;, but\u00a0only in\u00a0. In addition to the normal\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Buckler\"&gt;Buckler&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0properties, it offers +1 to\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0so long as it is worn.\nGameplay.\nCharacters with a &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; score of 20 begin naturally regenerating hit points at the rate of +1\u00a0hp/turn (1 turn = 10 rounds = 1 real time minute, or 10 minutes of in-game time).\nIf during character creation the player chooses a race of &lt;a href=\"Half-orc\"&gt;Half-orc&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Dwarf\"&gt;Dwarf&lt;/a&gt; and sets their Constitution to the max of 19, then equipping Buckley's Buckler will give &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; regeneration as soon as the &lt;a href=\"The%20Friendly%20Arm\"&gt;The Friendly Arm&lt;/a&gt;, in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20One\"&gt;Chapter One&lt;/a&gt;.\nOther races (except for Elves) will have to wait until they acquire the &lt;a href=\"Manual%20of%20Bodily%20Health\"&gt;Manual of Bodily Health&lt;/a&gt;. Elves cannot naturally regenerate at all in .\nMoreover, Buckley's Buckler allows &lt;a href=\"Barbarian\"&gt;Barbarian&lt;/a&gt; Half-orcs and Dwarves who start with 19 Constitution to reach 25 via the use of the aforementioned Manual of Bodily Health and &lt;a href=\"Barbarian%20Rage\"&gt;Barbarian Rage&lt;/a&gt;, allowing the character to regenerate 1hp every 10 seconds (6 seconds = 1 round, so it's just over 1.6 rounds) very early in BGEE. Though, of course, this is limited by the short duration of Barbarian Rage (5 rounds), but with two casts the 25 Constitution can be kept up for 10 rounds.\nFinally, the Constitution increase from this item can be used as emergency healing for certain characters, depending on their Constitution, class and level, as any hp increase gained from equipping it remains for as long as it stays equipped. For example, a badly injured level 9 &lt;a href=\"Eldoth%20Kron\"&gt;Eldoth&lt;/a&gt; (15 CON) that currently has 7hp and equips this shield (perhaps switching away from an equipped bow to a sword-and-shield setup) will get +9hp (current and maximum) as a result of it and, due to the fact equipping a shield or switching weapon sets is a \"free action\" in combat, he can still drink a potion of healing in the same round, meaning he can instantly get +18hp to go from a dangerous 7hp to a reasonably safe 25hp."}
{"id": "29029", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29029", "title": "Bugbear", "text": ""}
{"id": "37325", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37325", "title": "Bugbear Caverns", "text": "The Bugbear Caverns is an in \"\".\nDescription.\nIt is a short dungeon that makes up the second part of the caves on the way to the &lt;a href=\"ruined%20Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;ruined Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;, linking the &lt;a href=\"Wyrm%20Cave\"&gt;Wyrm Cave&lt;/a&gt; to the temple proper. It earns its name because it is home to a tribe of &lt;a href=\"bugbear\"&gt;bugbear&lt;/a&gt;s that the local &lt;a href=\"Cyric\"&gt;Cyric&lt;/a&gt; cult has made into their impromptu protectors.\nLayout.\nUpon entering, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; will be set upon by a large number of bugbears supported by a &lt;a href=\"Bugbear%20Veteran\"&gt;Bugbear Veteran&lt;/a&gt;. A tunnel to the south leads to the second of the three chambers, where &lt;a href=\"Snorgash\"&gt;Snorgash&lt;/a&gt; the Bugbear Chieftain awaits with more bugbears. A second tunnel leads east from the area where Snorgash is waiting, past a second southerly chamber with yet more bugbears, before culminating in the doorway into the ruined temple proper.\nA &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Shadow\"&gt;Greater Shadow&lt;/a&gt; is lurking near the opening to the second chamber, but can only be seen if a &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; member is wearing the &lt;a href=\"Spectacles%20of%20Spectacle\"&gt;Spectacles of Spectacle&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Zaviak%27s%20Vision%20Quest\"&gt;Zaviak's Vision Quest&lt;/a&gt;. If the right conversation topics are chosen or &lt;a href=\"Viconia%20DeVir\"&gt;Viconia DeVir&lt;/a&gt; is in the party, it may be sent against the nearby bugbears, although on most difficulty levels it will ultimately fall to &lt;a href=\"Flail%20%2B1\"&gt;Snorgash's enchanted weapon&lt;/a&gt; if not supported.\nTraps have been set both in the center of the first passageway and in the opening leading to the final band of bugbears. A chest in the final chambers is both locked and trapped.\nChests containing various loot are found in both the far reaches of the first chamber and in the third chamber."}
