{"id": "4624", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4624", "title": "Burning Hands", "text": "The Burning Hands\u00a0spell sends out 5-ft. jets of flame from the wizard's fingertips.\nDescription.\nThe area of effect can hit friendly targets.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, changing its effects and school. See below for description:\nBurning Hands\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Special\nDuration: Instant\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen the wizard casts this spell, a cone of searing flames shoots from his fingertips towards a designated point. His hands must be held so as to send forth a fan-like sheet of flames: the wizard\u2019s thumbs must touch each other, and his fingers must be spread. The burning hands send out 10-foot-long jets of flame in a horizontal arc of about 60 degrees in front of the wizard. All creatures caught in the flames suffer 1d6 points of fire damage plus 1d6 for every other 2 levels of the caster (up to a maximum of 5d6)."}
{"id": "27804", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27804", "title": "Burning Man", "text": "A Burning Man is a fire-based elemental golem. They appear similar to a Fire Elemental. \nThe Burning Man's melee attack weapon is a +3 enchanted item, with a reach of 1 and a speed factor of 0. Upon a successful hit, it deals 1d4 crushing damage with a strength damage bonus of +8. In addition, the attack also deals 1d8 fire damage and 1d4 magical energy damage.\nThe creature regenerates 1 hit point every second and is healed by fire damage. A +3 enchanted weapon or greater is needed to strike the Firey golem.\nBurning Men can innately produce a spell effect known as Cinder Ashes to cause fire damage and &lt;a href=\"blindness\"&gt;blindness&lt;/a&gt; to multiple party members. They can also &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; party members for 4 rounds if they fail a save vs spells with a -4 penalty (blocked by magic resistance, no magic school). If the character is not protected against the effect, the save must be made once every four rounds.\nAs of BG2EE 2.6 + the innate spell is entitled as Cinder Shower (SPIN560.SPL) and the &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; effect aura is called Keening (SPIN559.SPL).\nThe Cinder Shower is \"cast\" instantly and uses an AoE projectile identified as \"Sparkle Area Red\", about 15' in diameter. The effect has a 50' range. The innate spell will inflict 4d10 fire damage on all party members in the AoE, although magic resistance can block it. There is no saving throw. Additionally, the effect will also cause a 'Blindness'-like effect that impedes affected party members with a -4 THAC0 penalty and -2 Dexterity modifier lasting 5 rounds. The Blindness effect cannot be blocked by any protections, nor does it have a saving throw, and it bypasses magic resistance. The effect cannot be dispelled. An affected victim will have a \"blinded\" icon on their avatar portrait. However, it is not actually blindness, and the character still retains their usual visual range. \nThe Keening spell is \"cast\" instantly and has a 320 feet radius and only affects the player's party members. No spell immunity or spell protection will protect against the Keening. Magic resistance can block it. A saving throw vs. spells with a -4 penalty is needed to negate the effect or be under a Panic effect for 4-rounds.\nThey are first encountered in \"\".\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes a few changes to this creature."}
