{"id": "55864", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55864", "title": "CORNUGON.ITM", "text": "CORNUGON.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by various &lt;a href=\"Cornugon\"&gt;Cornugon&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nIt is considered a magical and +3 enchanted item and deals 1d6 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nA successful hit on a target requires a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs Breath to negate a 10 second duration &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect. &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can also block it.\nThe hit also exposes the target creature to a systemic &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; effect, inflicting 1 &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; per second for 10 seconds. There is no saving throw. Only resistance to the status effect or poison damage will block this."}
