{"id": "40156", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40156", "title": "Cambion (Watcher's Keep)", "text": "This Cambion can be found in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt; in this &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20-%20Cambion%20%28AR3007%29\"&gt;room&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThe cambion, which has a Death Knight animation sprite that appears to be wielding a large sword is initially observed by the party when in visual range.\nThe cambion can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;, and so it will most likely be able to immediately disappear from view by quaffing a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invisibility\"&gt;Potion of Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter that action, the area script in this room has a slight delay before additional reinforcements are created in the area.\nThe cambion behaves as a melee attacking creature, usually engaging the closest enemy. It can reapply invisibility with its remaining supply of potions as it battles the party.\nAlthough this is a demonic creature, unlike most other fiends in the Watcher's Keep, this particular opponent has no special protections against normal or magical weapons, status effects, and not even fire damage.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod revises the Cambion in moderate ways.\nAs the fiend is a Thief class, it now is assigned 1 pip in long sword weapon proficiency and one pip in single-weapon fighting style. The creature's final THAC0 is now improved, as well as armor class.\nAttacking from invisibility bestows a 4-point THAC0 bonus to hit. \nThe Bastard sword is replaced by a &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword%20%2B1\"&gt;Long Sword +1&lt;/a&gt;, so it can benefit from &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt; attacks.\nThe cambion begins battle from invisibility and can backstab with a X5 damage multiplier. Its Ai script will attempt to quaff a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invisibility\"&gt;Potion of Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; after each attack, to continue potential backstabbing during the fight. It carries 3 potions for this purpose."}
{"id": "27152", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27152", "title": "Camitis", "text": "Camitis is one of the kidnappers in the quest &lt;a href=\"Find%20the%20kidnappers%20who%20buried%20Tirdir\"&gt;Find the kidnappers who buried Tirdir&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nIf the party enters the &lt;a href=\"Kidnappers%27%20House\"&gt;Kidnappers' House&lt;/a&gt;, then there will be a confrontation. The events will differ depending on if Am-Si is allowed to flee into the house or if he is killed outside the building. \nAm-Si Alive.\nAm-Si: I'm sorry! I dont't know how he found out!\nCamitis: That ain't why we're mad, you little rock-gnawing fool! You were supposed to kill them sacks, not dump them!\nAm-Si: I... I couldn't! I can't... I can't stand the blood!\nCamitis: So drown 'em! Whack 'em with a stick! I don't care! What kind of...\nReti: We have to go, Camitis. We got company.\nCamitis: Not before I kill this little rat-stink! Not before!\nReti will flee from the house, Camitis kills Am-Si, and then attempts to flee as well.\nAm-Si Dead.\nCamitis: We heard you killin' our brethren outside! Damn your filthy blades for cuttin' that fool down! I'll do you right for that!\nReti: Not me, Camitis. Our deal is blown! I'm heading for the hills!\nReti flees the house, Camitis attacks &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; or nearest party member.\nNote that if Reti is engaged outside the home (because the party can be split so that some can enter and others may be outside), then Reti will fight back in melee combat.\nAs is sometimes the case in the unmodified game, the weapon proficiencies assigned may not be configured to match the creature's equipped fighting weapon, and thus, Camitis will suffer an unskilled THAC0 penalty in melee with his battle axe. This is calculated in the InfoBox. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a new default smarter fighter script to Camitis for better tactical behavior. SCS assigns 5 pips in Axe, and 2 pips in sword and shield fighting style. This will improve his THAC0, damage output and boost APR. His Armor class against missiles will boost by 4.\nAdditional SCS random treasures are placed in his inventory (DW#RND06 and 14)."}
