{"id": "13298", "revid": "225166", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13298", "title": "Caravan Tent", "text": "The Caravan Tent is a red tent southeast of the exterior wall of &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nInside, prior to &lt;a href=\"Dealing%20with%20the%20Trademeet%20genies\"&gt;Dealing with the Trademeet genies&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Caravan%20Merchant\"&gt;Caravan Merchant&lt;/a&gt; laments that he has nothing to sell.\nAfter the djinn situation is resolved, &lt;a href=\"Caravan%20Merchant\"&gt;his store&lt;/a&gt; is open for business.\nThe bookshelf to the left holds &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23Poor%20treasure\"&gt;poor random treasure&lt;/a&gt;, while the center bookshelf has &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23Average%20treasure\"&gt;average random treasure&lt;/a&gt;; neither have any traps or alarms."}
{"id": "2119", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2119", "title": "Carbos", "text": "Carbos is one of the two assassins who tries to murder &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt;. He approaches the Ward after entering the &lt;a href=\"Bunkhouse\"&gt;Bunkhouse&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen Gorion's Ward reaches the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, conversation with &lt;a href=\"Sanadal%20Gwist\"&gt;Sanadal Gwist&lt;/a&gt; reveals that Carbos is her cousin.\nDialogue.\n\"'Ere there. You're Gorion's little whelp, aren't ya? Yeah, you match the description. You don't look so dangerous to me.\"\nClearly, none of the dialogue options will allow you to avoid a fight.\nIf you haven't encountered &lt;a href=\"Shank\"&gt;Shank&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Priests%27%20Quarters\"&gt;Priests' Quarters&lt;/a&gt; yet, a &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; entry will appear when you leave the building.\n&lt;a href=\"Karan\"&gt;Karan&lt;/a&gt; approaches upon exiting, as he \"heard shouting.\"\nBaldur's Gate II.\nBoth Carbos and Shank return (somehow) in . They are found in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;, the capital city of &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt;, where they fight over a woman named &lt;a href=\"Bubbles\"&gt;Bubbles&lt;/a&gt;. The victor is randomly determined, though Bubbles leaves out of boredom regardless of who survives."}
