{"id": "6167", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6167", "title": "Carlig", "text": "Carlig is a &lt;a href=\"duergar\"&gt;duergar&lt;/a&gt; merchant who can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. He is partners with fellow duergar's &lt;a href=\"Finderlig\"&gt;Finderlig&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Uder%20Mordin\"&gt;Uder Mordin&lt;/a&gt;. Carlig is also a shopkeeper and buys and sells goods. His prices can change depending on your appearance as surfacers or drow.\nBuy and Sell.\nWhen he recognizes the party as surface dwellers one should probably avoid him or just steal everything the party desperately needs. His prices are inflated and his stock is limited:\nDrow Disguised.\nOnce you've received your disguise, go see him again for a more attractive pricing model, a more hospitable tone, a better range of items and the additional service of fencing stolen materials. Be aware though, that he's less trusting of Drow (who'd have thought) and pays a little better attention if the party's trying to obtain items without paying."}
{"id": "2748", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2748", "title": "Carnival", "text": ""}
{"id": "2761", "revid": "3482277", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2761", "title": "Carnival Merchants", "text": ""}
{"id": "2775", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2775", "title": "Carnival Shops", "text": "There are a number of merchants who have set up small stores inside tents in the &lt;a href=\"Carnival\"&gt;Carnival&lt;/a&gt; area. One specializes in &lt;a href=\"Potion%20Tent\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt; although the two he has for sale seem a bit odd and he doesn't buy anything. The other four merchants will sell and buy items. Each of the four specializes in a different category of items for sale and each has a short list of items they won't purchase. \nAll of the tents contain lootable containers but only the Armor Tent merchant will alert the authorities if a thief is observed pilfering his wares.\nMagic Items Tent.\nThis merchant will not buy armor or shields of any type."}
{"id": "9251", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9251", "title": "Carras", "text": "Carras is a smuggler working under Esamon, also known as &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt;, in &lt;a href=\"Amkethran\"&gt;Amkethran&lt;/a&gt;. He is also a \"shop keeper\", and will open a store function, available for only one visit to the cave. Side Note: Apparently, based on the accents of Esamon and Carras, there is a part of the Faer\u00fbn which is similar to Australia.\nThe first time in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%208\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 8&lt;/a&gt; when you enter the &lt;a href=\"Smuggler%27s%20Cave\"&gt;Smuggler's Cave&lt;/a&gt; in Amkethran, you will see some of &lt;a href=\"Balthazar\"&gt;Balthazar's&lt;/a&gt; monks shutting the smugglers' business down. Regardless of whether you help the smugglers or not, you can trade with Carras, although you can only do it once. \nIf you don't enter the cave in Chapter 8, you will have missed your chance, even if you go in the Smuggler's Cave in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%209\"&gt;Chapter 9&lt;/a&gt;. For a more detailed look at the first encounter of Carras and the Monks visit the &lt;a href=\"Smuggler%27s%20Cave\"&gt;Smuggler's Cave&lt;/a&gt; area article. \nGameplay.\nCarras has an adjusted pickpocketing score of 125% - which will make it tougher for a party member to steal from him.\nIf attacked by the party - Carras will initially force cast &lt;a href=\"Mass%20Invisibility\"&gt;Mass Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf able, he'll attempt a &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Normal Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, then cast a &lt;a href=\"Horror\"&gt;Horror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Hold Person (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Carrion%20Summons\"&gt;Carrion Summons&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote that this smuggler has an innate 63% &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe items in his quick slots (&lt;a href=\"Enkidu%27s%20Full%20Plate\"&gt;Enkidu's Full Plate&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"K%27logarath\"&gt;K'logarath&lt;/a&gt;) are flagged as unstealable, but can be dropped upon death. The same applies to the &lt;a href=\"Gargoyle%20Boots\"&gt;Gargoyle Boots&lt;/a&gt; he wears.\nCarras is scripted to use his bow and arrow attacks over melee fighting.\nDiscount (exploit).\n Helping the smugglers will make Carras give you a discount. He then will sell for only 99% of the regular item value (opposed to 140% without discount) and buy items for a rate of 80% of their value (30% without discount). With high &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Charisma\"&gt;Charisma&lt;/a&gt; this can lead to a situation where a unique, high valued item, e.g. &lt;a href=\"Enkidu%27s%20Full%20Plate\"&gt;Enkidu's Full Plate&lt;/a&gt; from his own stock, can be sold back to him for more coin than it originally cost when buying \u2013 effectively letting &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; gain coin through trade, here.\n This exploit no longer works in the enhanced edition, since the buy markup is set to 30%.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; Mod addresses an oddity. Dialogue in the game suggests that the smugglers buy and sell stolen goods, however the unmodded game does not allow them to behave as a fence. The Mod changes this (it is the only fence available in ToB). The shop's inventory is modified slightly to include some Mod specific items.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a different smarter mage script to Carras. He gets a fully populated spell book commensurate with his mage XP level, and will initialize different spells for protection, such as &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;SI Divination&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Dispelling Screen\" with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and others.\nHe can try a few spell removals and a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt;.\nExpect a &lt;a href=\"Mordenkainen%27s%20Sword\"&gt;Mordenkainen's Sword&lt;/a&gt; to assist him in battle. A Spell Sequencer with a triple &lt;a href=\"Dire%20Charm\"&gt;Dire Charm&lt;/a&gt; can be instantly launched, and a minor sequencer as well.\nBuy and Sell.\nBelow is the listing for the discounted store."}
{"id": "11052", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11052", "title": "Carrion Crawler", "text": "Carrion Crawlers resemble giant grubs and can be found in caves, sewers or occasionally wandering in the wilderness. They tend to travel in groups of at least two (though they can be encountered alone) and can both paralyse their targets in combat and transmit diseases."}
{"id": "5844", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5844", "title": "Carrion Summons", "text": "When cast, Carrion Summons allows a wizard to summon forth one or two &lt;a href=\"Carrion%20Crawler\"&gt;carrion crawler&lt;/a&gt; creatures and command them.\nGameplay.\nThe wizard selects a location on the area map where the carrion crawler(s) are to spawn, with a 25-foot distance range using the targeting cursor.\nWhen the casting time is finished, one or two creatures will appear on the map and be ready to receive commands.\nThis spell's maximum duration caps at caster level 20, lasting up to about 26 rounds and a few extra seconds.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced D&amp;D 2nd Edition ruleset has no equivalent spell. It appears that Bioware just made up this spell on its own.\nGallery.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced the \"Carrion Summons\" with the spell described below:\nAnimate Skeleton Warrior\nLevel: 6\nSchool: Necromancy\nRange: Long\nDuration: 8 hours\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nThis spell animates the corpse of a skilled warrior to rise up and serve the caster. This powerful undead creature will remain under the caster\u2019s control until slain or the spell duration expires.\nSkeleton Warrior (9 Hit Dice):\nSTR 18/51, DEX 14, CON -, INT 15, WIS 14, CHA 12; AL Neutral Evil\nHP 108, AC 2, THAC0 11, Saving Throws 5/7/6/5/8\n2 Attacks Per Round, 2d6+4 Slashing Damage (Two-Handed Sword +1)\nSpecial Qualities:\nImmune to normal weapons\nImmune to charm, confusion, hold, poison, sleep, stun, &amp; death effects\nCold Resistance 100%; Magic Resistance 90%\nSlashing &amp; Piercing Resistance 40%; Missile Resistance 60%"}
