{"id": "7709", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7709", "title": "Carsa", "text": "Carsa calls to you from the northern basin of the former Firewine River in the &lt;a href=\"Firewine%20Bridge\"&gt;Firewine Bridge&lt;/a&gt; area (&lt;a href=\"Coordinates\"&gt;3500.920&lt;/a&gt;) as soon as you come into sight.\nShe was a member of an adventuring party exploring &lt;a href=\"Firewine%20Ruins\"&gt;Firewine Ruins&lt;/a&gt; until they found a jar with &lt;a href=\"Kahrk\"&gt;Kahrk&lt;/a&gt;, a 12th level Ogre Mage, trapped inside. He then proceeded to drive them all insane until they killed themselves one by one, until finally only Carsa remained with the jar. If you demand the jar, she will commit suicide by freeing the Ogre Mage trapped inside it. Then it's your turn.\nDialog.\nThere are many paths through the dialog, leading to either abandoning Carsa, in which case she walks out of the game, or\u2014eventually\u2014demanding the jar from her. The most direct route to the latter is 1, 1, 2, 2, 2 which is shown below. Other dialog options lead to no other useful or interesting information.\n\"He's driving me... mad! Oh, please make it stop, make him stop his screaming. AAAHhhhhhh...! Shut it up!\"\nCharmed.\nSelected Dialog - \"Dead gonna drag you under when I'm done.\"\nNo other change."}
{"id": "4570", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4570", "title": "Carsomyr", "text": "Carsomyr, also known as The Holy Avenger, is a powerful two-handed sword which can only be wielded by non-evil aligned &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s. This limits the use of the weapon to a paladin &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Keldorn%20Firecam\"&gt;Keldorn&lt;/a&gt;, or those with access to &lt;a href=\"Use%20Any%20Item\"&gt;Use Any Item&lt;/a&gt;.\nCarsomyr +5.\nAcquisition.\nIn \"\", it can normally be obtained by slaying the red dragon &lt;a href=\"Firkraag\"&gt;Firkraag&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;Firkraag's Hideout&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt's also technically possible to steal this weapon (along with the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20the%20Shield\"&gt;Cloak of the Shield&lt;/a&gt;) from Firkraag, though one must first reduce the dragon's size without angering it, to make pickpocketing possible - for example, via &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Surge\"&gt;Wild Surge&lt;/a&gt; #13, to temporarily turn it into a spirit wolf.\nGameplay.\nThe on-hit dispel effect is coded as a Wizard spell and will summon the &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizards\"&gt;Cowled Wizards&lt;/a&gt; while in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. The daily use charge ability is of the &lt;a href=\"Priest%20spells%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;priest type&lt;/a&gt; though and won't attract their attention.\nThe on-hit dispel magic effect works as described, and it applies a schooless dispel effect that has no secondary type assigned - &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;SI: Abjuration&lt;/a&gt; cannot block the on-hit dispel magic effect. \nThe daily use dispel magic charges don't work as described. See the \"Bugs\" section below.\nThe level 30 dispel magic on-hit effect will not trigger if the weapon is made ineffective because the target is protected from being struck - for example by a &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt; spell. Note that a &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; won't prevent the on-hit dispel effect.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; bestowed by Carsomyr is coded to provide the wielder with a flat value modifier, not a cumulative value modifier. \nThe practical in-game effect of this not transparent to the player. There are some effects that can add onto the weapon's flat value, such as certain bard songs. Equipping another item that provides magic resistance can also add onto the flat value, but the player may have to equip the item before the sword, or even afterwards to have the cumulative MR values take effect and display on the character record properly.\nSome examples of the interactions found with this set value mechanic are given below:\nKeldorn has Carsomyr equipped, and quaffs a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Magic%20Protection\"&gt;Potion of Magic Protection&lt;/a&gt; = MR is 100%.\nKeldorn has already quaffed a Potion of Magic protection and then equips Carsomyr = MR is 100%.\nKeldorn has the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Gaxx\"&gt;Ring of Gaxx&lt;/a&gt; equipped, and then equips Carsomyr = MR is 50%.\nKeldorn has Carsomyr equipped and then adds the Ring of Gaax = MR is 60%.\nKeldorn is wearing the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Cloak of Balduran&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Amulet%20of%20Seldarine\"&gt;Amulet of Seldarine&lt;/a&gt; = MR is 35%. He then equips Carsomyr = MR is 50%\nKeldorn has the sword equipped. A mage casts &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Resistance\"&gt;Lower Resistance&lt;/a&gt; from a scroll upon him. MR is 30%. He then reequips Carsomyr = MR is 30%\nBugs.\nAlthough this weapon's description claims that its castable Dispel Magic (SPPR303) ability is cast at level 15, it actually doesn't work as written. Instead, the casting level is determined by and scales with the wielder's \"divine\" caster level. \nIf the wielder has no divine spell casting levels by virtue of its assigned class - then the dispel magic cast from the sword will be the lowest divine casting level - which is level 1.\nOn tests with a level 30 Thief (with &lt;a href=\"Use%20Any%20Item\"&gt;Use Any Item&lt;/a&gt;) and a level 30 paladin, the thief was unable to dispel a level 8 bard's Mirror Image using this weapon's &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Dispel Magic (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, whereas the paladin was able to do it consistently. \nCarsomyr +6.\nAcquisition.\nIn \"\", &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt; can upgrade Carsomyr +5 to its +6 version if the protagonist is willing to use the &lt;a href=\"Eye%20of%20Tyr\"&gt;Eye of Tyr&lt;/a&gt; and spend .\nAchievements.\nThe Holy Sword.\nRecover Carsomyr, the Holy Avenger."}
