{"id": "36224", "revid": "53032777", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36224", "title": "Casque of Dragomir", "text": "Game Play.\nFrom a practical standpoint, this Casque serves the purpose of allowing &lt;a href=\"Hexxat\"&gt;Hexxat&lt;/a&gt; and party members to \"Tomb Walk\" between houses of the dead. From the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt; to another Tomb or Crypt elsewhere can be reached via a sort of teleportation. After the quest is complete, the Casque allows a return to the graveyard starting point.\nDuring Throne of Bhaal, the Casque of Dragomir will be upgraded with &lt;a href=\"Shroud%20of%20the%20Unproved\"&gt;Shroud of the Unproved&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"The%20Claw%20of%20the%20Black%20Leopard\"&gt;The Claw of the Black Leopard&lt;/a&gt; to create the &lt;a href=\"Casque%20of%20Entrapment\"&gt;Casque of Entrapment&lt;/a&gt;. It removes the requirement to find a graveyard to \"Tomb Walk\"."}
{"id": "8556", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8556", "title": "Casson Belde'ar", "text": "Casson Belde'ar is a boy who was killed for trespassing on grounds belonging to the temple of &lt;a href=\"Umberlee\"&gt;Umberlee&lt;/a&gt;. His &lt;a href=\"Tremain%20Belde%27ar\"&gt;father&lt;/a&gt; asks you to obtain and return to him the boy's body while it can still be resurrected. Their &lt;a href=\"Tremain%20Belde%27ar%27s%20Home\"&gt;home&lt;/a&gt; is located in &lt;a href=\"West%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;West Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. Upon a successful resurrection of the lad, he then receives a good tongue lashing from his father.\nDialogue.\n\"cough\"... wha...?\nFather, I... what's going on?\nWhat... but... but it wasn't my faul...\nBut I... we... I'm sorr...\nBut... I... awe..."}
