{"id": "51272", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51272", "title": "Cave (Spellhold Test)", "text": "This area is technically part of &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis cave will be a location that the party is transferred to by the Asylum Apparition, depending on how the party answered certain questions as part of the Tests necessary to leave spell hold. Dialogue options and subsequent responses from the party will determine if this particular area is presented as an additional test, most likely as part of the harder or more difficult path. This cave has no connection to any other area, so the player cannot gather the party and travel in the traditional method to another area.\nGameplay.\nThe party is transported to this area, to face a hostile group of creatures in battle, for the purpose of presenting a more difficult path forward, possibly even as punishment for words said earlier in the previous testing area.\nWhen the party arrives here, they have only a few seconds before a group of hostile Earth-based creatures' attack. The Umber Hulk and mephits will likely be able to launch some of their innate spell abilities at the outset of hostilities. When the creatures are defeated, another appearance of the &lt;a href=\"Apparition%20%28Spellhold%29\"&gt;Apparition&lt;/a&gt; will occur.\nThe Apparition will await the party to initiate dialogue:\nThe party is presented with several dialogue selections to choose from.\nIf the party replies with \"I refuse to speak to you anymore. You are little more than a mindless golem.\" - then the Apparition will reply \"That may well be, but I must still fulfill the duty that I am assigned. Were I living and breathing, your fate would be the same. The path gets harder still.\" \nIf the party says \"It is wasted as it is. Would that it had the fertile nature of the previous room.\" then the Apparition remarks \"A naive view, but a hopeful one. Had I a soul, I am sure I would be moved. So be it; I will take this as a good sign, though I find your mind to be more complicated than these simple tests illustrate.\"\nAnother possible answer is \"I shall raze the entire building to this condition.\" to which the Apparition replies \"Unproductive. You are not responding to these evaluations well at all. Would that I had a director here to study you properly. As it stands, I can only discourage the thoughts. The path gets harder.\" \nAnd the last reply is \"I have no insight as to why it is like this. Should I worry over what I cannot help?\" and the Apparition says \"I suppose this view is unavoidable, since I reinforce it by subjecting you to the tests in the first. Very well. This acceptance shall be taken as a good sign. The path is made easier.\"\"\nContainers.\nThere are four \"craters\" in the cave that can be searched, and various items are available for the taking. There is a &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt; as well as plenty of mundane and enchanted arrows, bolts and bullets. There are also a Crossbow and Longbow. Note that if the containers within are not searched before speaking with the Apparition there won't be an opportunity to loot them before being whisked away from the cave. "}
{"id": "11039", "revid": "4896558", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11039", "title": "Cave Bear", "text": "Cave Bears are particularly aggressive bears usually found in woodland areas and caves. They typically travel alone, though they can be found in pairs. They drop no items. Unlike black and brown bears, cave bears will attack on sight."}
{"id": "23434", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23434", "title": "Cave Between Underdark and Exit from Underdark", "text": " Plot Warning: Using the exit (177, 653) moves the plot forward to chapter 6.\nThis area is also known as Elven Temple Ruins, there\u2019s a skirmish going on here, and it\u2019s only a few steps away from the surface. \nThis area has traditionally been patrolled and monitored by &lt;a href=\"Adalon\"&gt;Adalon&lt;/a&gt; to ensure that hostilities between the drow and surface elves doesn't get out of control. With Irenicus schemes in play, that balance has been lost for the moment.\nDescription.\nThe area is part natural cavern, and an underground series of connected rooms that are part of a dilapidated and damaged elven temple.\nGameplay.\nThe party will enter a natural cavern from the &lt;a href=\"Kuo%20Toa%20in%20Underdark\"&gt;Western Tunnels&lt;/a&gt;. As soon as the party transitions here a hidden map sector triggers a spell effect that removes the drow illusion that is upon the party from &lt;a href=\"Adalon\"&gt;Adalon&lt;/a&gt;. If the party never had it (unlikely but possible) then it won't affect anything noticeable to the player.\nThe party observes a scattered group of drow , as well as a &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Spider\"&gt;Giant Spider&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Huge%20Spider\"&gt;Huge Spider&lt;/a&gt; arachnids. There are five drow here, all armed. Four are male and female fighters and there is one male wizard. \nEverything in this cavern will be hostile immediately. Fight your way through to an opening on the North wall and continue on to the elven temple ruins.\nThe next room has two closed doors, one to the north and one to the west. Inside is a female drow warrior and three War Elves. Upon entry a text will display:\nThe party can help fight the drow or just press on.\nThe room to north has more action going on, with a three-on-three battle between drow and elven warriors. There are two \"containers\" on the floor rubble/a fallen warrior's corpse that can be examined for found items.\nOpening the doorway to the west has yet another melee happening. This time 5 drow are up against 6 elves. On the floor within is another fallen corpse that can be examined.\nA closed door to the west is available leading to a small room with rubble and debris and another door leading to the exit to the surface on the north wall. Several elves have already told the party to make for the surface and to see someone called &lt;a href=\"Elhan\"&gt;Elhan&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce the drow are dead, which can be hastened with help from the party, all the surviving elves will leave the temple ruins.\nThe party can transition to the surface when they are ready. Note that it won't make much sense to take any drow equipment with you top side.\nNotes.\nThe elves in this area are difficult to turn hostile through deliberate/accidental attacks or damaging them with errant AoE damage. However, they will eventually become hostile on an individual basis. Making one, few, or all of the elves hostile will not damage party reputation and has no effect on the how the surface elves in the next area will react.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod will add and revise the scripts of the drow in this area. The drow wizard will let loose some buffs and spells. The warriors will have revised weapon proficiencies commensurate with their XP levels and furnished weaponry.\nAdditional drow will be placed in this area with the mod, depending on components installed and the game difficulty setting.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Eilistraee%27s%20Song\"&gt;Eilistraee's Song&lt;/a&gt; mod will place &lt;a href=\"Solaufein\"&gt;Solaufein&lt;/a&gt; in the final room with the exit to the surface door. The party must initiate dialogue to trigger essential mod scripts and a &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt; addition."}
