{"id": "19591", "revid": "275615", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19591", "title": "Cave of the Dead", "text": "The Cave of the Dead is a location inside &lt;a href=\"Amkethran\"&gt;Amkethran&lt;/a&gt; where the quest of &lt;a href=\"The%20Graveyard%20Lich\"&gt;The Graveyard Lich&lt;/a&gt; takes place. To gain access to the Cave, you must get &lt;a href=\"Marlowe\"&gt;Marlowe&lt;/a&gt; to agree to pass a message to the guardian monk and allow your entry. The party cannot enter the cave unless they are engaged in the quest.\nInside you will meet with &lt;a href=\"Vongoethe\"&gt;Vongoethe&lt;/a&gt;, the Lich at the center of this quest.\nThere are traps on the doors on the balconies in the north of this area, if you disarm them yourself it will net you at least 16.000 XP.\nThere are four tables on the raised platform, equally spaced apart. These tables may be interacted with (\"clicked on'). Each Table will spawn monsters (yielding a total of 110.000 XP) and disarm some of the traps that are set on the balcony and doors (reached by climbing ladders). If you wish to gain XP by disarming the traps yourself, do that before clicking on the tables:\nOne of the doors is an entrance to\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Monastery_%28Amkethran%29\"&gt;Balthazar's Monastery&lt;/a&gt; However, it will be impassable if you have not already made certain progress in the adventure.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some changes to the abilities of the spawns. For instance, the Greater Air Elementals will employ a \"whirlwind\" attack similar to the HLA. It also has a chance to implement an instant death effect. The Ice Golems deal very strong Cone of Cold attacks that bypass most magic defenses and magic resistance. "}
{"id": "35296", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35296", "title": "Cayia", "text": "Cayia is a courtesan living on &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt; when &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and their party arrive to seek out &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;. She is supposed to be the exclusive lover of &lt;a href=\"Desharik\"&gt;Desharik&lt;/a&gt; but is secretly cheating on him. There is no real opportunity to pick pocket this creature, nor to attack and kill her - and she poses no threat to the party in any ensuing battle around Desharik's ship.\nGameplay.\nShe is only encountered as part of the quest &lt;a href=\"Leaving%20the%20island\"&gt;Leaving the island&lt;/a&gt;, when &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt; sends the party to steal the &lt;a href=\"Pirate%20Horn\"&gt;Pirate Horn&lt;/a&gt; that is in her possession. When a party member enters (there is no requirement for the entire party to enter and \"gather your party\") - that party member will discover her in the sack with a fling named \"Algor\", her latest bed buddy. \nAfter the party pilfers the Pirate Horn from her quarters, she will flee to Desharik's ship at the docks. When the party arrives there later, she will join Desharik in confronting the party, but Desharik will use this opportunity to reveal he is aware of her infidelity, cutting her down where she stands for betraying him."}
{"id": "24772", "revid": "3539497", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24772", "title": "Celestial", "text": ""}
{"id": "5389", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5389", "title": "Celestial Fury", "text": "Celestial Fury is a unique &lt;a href=\"katana%20%2B3\"&gt;katana +3&lt;/a&gt; that can be obtained from a specific encounter in and the Enhanced Edition game version.\nGameplay.\nThe weapon strikes a +3 enchanted item. \nIt inflicts 1d10+3 points of &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nEach successful hit exposes the target to a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect unless that is negated by a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Spell. If the save is failed, the target is stunned for one round. The stun effect is not blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; or Spell Protections such as &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;. If the target is affected by the stun, the combat log will display \"\"Stunned\" and a 3D graphic effect (SPFLSRIN) will play over the target. The katana's description notes this ability as \"Booming Thunder\"\", however the combat log won't display this term anywhere. \nAdditionally. each hit on a target has a 5% probability of applying 20 &lt;a href=\"Electricity%20damage\"&gt;Electricity damage&lt;/a&gt; to the target as well. This is non magical elemental damage and can't be blocked or prevented by anything, however protection from electricity damage type can mitigate it. The katana's description notes this as a \"Shocking Blow\" ability - but the combat log won't display this term anywhere.\nThe blade has two abilities that can be selected from the wielder's item use button. Each ability can be used once per day - and they recharge after a standard 8-hour resting cycle:\nNote.\n Despite being called \"Lightning Strike\", this ability works similarly to a level 10+ &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt; (the in-game log even calls it \"Lightning Bolt\"), bouncing on walls, being treated as a level 3 spell and so on. It's also considered an Invocation/Evocation for the purposes of Mage kit spell school specialization. \nAchievements.\nFury of the Heavens.\nAcquire the Celestial Fury blade."}
