{"id": "27192", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27192", "title": "Chak", "text": "Chak is a member of &lt;a href=\"Samia\"&gt;Samia's&lt;/a&gt; relic hunter party.\nGameplay.\nThis male Ogre with an Orog-elite appearance will spawn at the designated location when Samia's group is triggered by script to appear.\nThe big brute attacks in melee combat wielding an enchanted battle axe and guarding self with the enchanted large shield.\nNotes.\nThe creature gains no benefit in the unmodified game from its assigned weapon proficiency, since it uses a battle axe and not a Morningstar/flail weapon. \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a few changes to Chak. The Orog/Ogre has a new SCS tactical combat AI for improved combat targeting and behavior. \n4 pips in battle axe weapon proficiency are assigned, and 2 pips in sword and shield fighting style. THAC0 and weapon damage will improve, as well as &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt;, and armor class vs. Missiles will boost by -4.\nSCS improves Chak's saving throws a wee bit to match up with a fighter class - even though its class is still an Ogre."}
{"id": "51555", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51555", "title": "Chalinthra", "text": "Chalinthra is a drow fighter/cleric and a potential dueling opponent available in the Ust Natha Tavern. Speak with &lt;a href=\"Sondal\"&gt;Sondal&lt;/a&gt;, the Duel Arena Manager in order to participate in the duels offered.\nGameplay.\nOnce the party member faces off to duel Chalinthra - the battle will be enjoined and she shall release a series of uninterruptible self-buffs to include &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20of%20the%20Archons\"&gt;Shield of the Archons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Regeneration%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Regeneration (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is worth pointing out that the InfoBox's memorized spells listed are not a completely accurate reflection of what her script may do during a battle sequence.\nShe'll try a &lt;a href=\"Silence%2C%2015%27%20Radius\"&gt;Silence, 15' Radius&lt;/a&gt; if her opponent has any mage or cleric class markers. She will attempt to cast a &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; on self when only 20% of her HP remains. There is another spell trigger available in the fight to apply &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Fire\"&gt;Protection From Fire&lt;/a&gt;.\nOffensively expect a &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20of%20Glory\"&gt;Bolt of Glory&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Symbol%2C%20Stun\"&gt;Symbol, Stun&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Person%20or%20Mammal\"&gt;Charm Person or Mammal&lt;/a&gt; and a touch attack using &lt;a href=\"Harm\"&gt;Harm&lt;/a&gt;. If able, she'll summon help using the &lt;a href=\"Animate%20Dead\"&gt;Animate Dead&lt;/a&gt; spell. Also, a &lt;a href=\"True%20Seeing\"&gt;True Seeing&lt;/a&gt; is available if certain conditions are met (such as the opponent being invisible).\nIn between spell casts, she'll wield her flail if the opponent comes close to her.\nIf slain, then the duel is over, and the party member gets her XP reward. Speak with Sondal again to continue with more duel opportunities if desired.\nBugs.\nNo drow innate magic resistance is assigned to Chalinthra. She should have some in the mid 70 percentile range based on other drow Underdark creature files. \nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some minor changes to her creature scripts, and abilities. An SCS Cleric AI script is supplied for more intelligent attack and defense behavior, as well as spell use. Chalinthra now has 2-pips in Flail weapon proficiency and 2 pips in sword and shield weapon style.\nWith this mod, she will instantly prepare for battle with (previously cast) &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Fire%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Protection From Fire (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Righteous%20Magic\"&gt;Righteous Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe is scripted to apply &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Serious%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Serious Wounds&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; spell on self if certain conditions are met.\nWithe the \"Smarter Priests\" component, her AI will be looking for various protective buffs, equipped items and opponent class conditions to help determine appropriate vulnerabilities for offensive or disabling spell casts. She will attempt to clear clouds with &lt;a href=\"Zone%20of%20Sweet%20Air\"&gt;Zone of Sweet Air&lt;/a&gt;.\nAll sorts of Priest spells are available to attack with, including various cause wounds, &lt;a href=\"Slay%20Living\"&gt;Slay Living&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Unholy%20Blight\"&gt;Unholy Blight&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Hold Person (priest)&lt;/a&gt; and many more.\nNote that with her initial buffs, if left in place and not removed her physical stats will be much improved and will fight in melee combat at an increased ability - striking more easily and dealing more damage with her flail."}
{"id": "48824", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48824", "title": "Chalmers", "text": "Chalmers is a halfling servant found in &lt;a href=\"Bloodbark%20Grove\"&gt;Bloodbark Grove&lt;/a&gt;. He is hired by the noble titled &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Dushwick\"&gt;Lord Dushwick&lt;/a&gt;. Lord Dushwick has tasked Chalmers with carrying his belonging on their journey and Chalmers seems to be having a difficult time with it. Upon encountering the duo the noble asks for the Warden's help in assisting Chalmers in a most irritated manner."}
{"id": "4754", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4754", "title": "Champion's Strength", "text": "Champion's Strength is a 5th level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; that allows the priest to draw strength from the divine and lend it to an ally.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this Divine spell, revising its effects, duration, casting time and description. See below:\nChampion's Strength\nLevel: 5\nSchool: Alteration\nSphere: Law\nRange: Medium\nDuration: 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, the priest draws on the power of his god and lends it to the target creature, in effect creating a champion. The target gains a bonus to strength, dexterity, and constitution scores at a rate of 1 for every 3 levels of the caster, up to a maximum bonus of 6 at 18th level. The effect lasts for 1 round for every level of the caster or until dispelled. This spell is not cumulative with itself or with other similar spells."}
{"id": "46542", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46542", "title": "Chan", "text": "Chan is one of the Elemental Princes of Air, who may be summoned through the casting of &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Summoning\"&gt;Elemental Summoning&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Elemental%20Summoning\"&gt;Greater Elemental Summoning&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "50321", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50321", "title": "Chandrilla", "text": "Chandrilla is one of the &lt;a href=\"Adventuring%20Party%20%28Underdark%29\"&gt;Adventuring Party (Underdark)&lt;/a&gt; members encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nIf given enough time the Priest will self-buff and then begin casting offensive oriented or disabling spells at enemies. \nHe will open up with a chain of \"force cast\" preparatory spells to include &lt;a href=\"Chant\"&gt;Chant&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Strength%20of%20One\"&gt;Strength of One&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;. Some of these AoE buffs may be applied to allies at the start of the conflict if they are near enough to the caster.\nA &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt; is scripted for further protection on self if a Fighter class opponent is detected. He can attempt a &lt;a href=\"Righteous%20Magic\"&gt;Righteous Magic&lt;/a&gt; on self as well a few rounds into the battle.\n&lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Fear\"&gt;Cloak of Fear&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Hold Person (priest)&lt;/a&gt; spells will be the go-to offensive spell casts, unless he is heavily wounded, then a &lt;a href=\"Earthquake\"&gt;Earthquake&lt;/a&gt; will be attempted.\nVarious healing magics are also scripted for use based on self and allies wounded thresholds being reached. Allies in close proximity might be healed the priest. A &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; spell is reserved for himself when near death.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod changes this cleric. The cleric has some new memorized spells added, and if the \"Smarter Priests\" component is installed, will more quickly prepare a defensive buff at the outset of hostilities. An SCS Priest script is provided for better and smarter AI behavior. An SCS random treasure is in the creature's inventory.\nHe will likely be protected by &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action\"&gt;Free Action&lt;/a&gt;.\nChandrilla will conjure a &lt;a href=\"Spiritual%20Hammer\"&gt;Spiritual Hammer&lt;/a&gt; during this preparatory chain of previously cast spells as well, and this will act as a melee and ranged weapon with the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod is installed, this creature's memorized spells and casts will be the SR versions."}
{"id": "47984", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47984", "title": "Chanelle the Maid", "text": "Chanelle the Maid is one of two maids who are found on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"De%27Arnise%20Keep\"&gt;de'Arnise Keep&lt;/a&gt; if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is a fighter and has accepted the keep as a stronghold following it's &lt;a href=\"The%20de%27Arnise%20Keep%20has%20been%20Invaded\"&gt;liberation&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"TorGal\"&gt;TorGal&lt;/a&gt; and his trolls. She is involved in one of the problems that Gorion's Ward must deal with as master of the keep.\n\nChanelle has been a maid within the keep most of her life. She was an orphan, and the de'Arnise family took her in as a servant when she was young. Now that she has reached adulthood, there are two suitors who desire her hand in marriage. Since the Lord of the keep is considered her guardian, it is up to that individual to decide which of the men has the Lord's blessing for the marriage."}
