{"id": "5044", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5044", "title": "Chant", "text": "Chant is a 2nd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; that acts as a dual-purpose buff and debuff, granting numerous bonuses to allies and imposing numerous penalties on enemies.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell, revising its description. See below:\nChant\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Conjuration\nSphere: Combat\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: None\nBy means of the Chant spell, the priest brings special favor upon himself and his party, and causes harm to his enemies. When the chant is completed, all attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws made by those in the area of effect who are friendly to the priest gain +1 bonuses, while those of the priest\u2019s enemies suffer -1 penalties. Multiple Chant spells are not cumulative.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "8554", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8554", "title": "Chanthalas Ulbright", "text": "Chanthalas Ulbright is a cleric offering services in &lt;a href=\"The%20Lady%27s%20Hall\"&gt;The Lady's Hall&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4867", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4867", "title": "Chaos", "text": "Chaos spell may cause the &lt;a href=\"Confused\"&gt;Confused&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effect&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a target point on the map to direct the spell towards, and the spell has a 35' range from the caster.\nWhen cast, a sparkling projectile travels to the designated targeting point and expands in 30 feet radius circle area of effect.\nNon-party creatures present in this spell's area of effect are potentially adversely exposed and must roll a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell with a -4 penalty or suffer the affects.\nLow level Non-party creatures get no saving throw if they have only 4 hit dice or lower.\nVictims who fail their save will be afflicted with a &lt;a href=\"Confused\"&gt;Confused&lt;/a&gt; effect for the spell's duration, as calculated by the caster's level.\nPlayer characters affected by this spell will show a \"Chaos\" special effect Icon (No. 47) on their portrait.\nAny creature that fails its save also triggers a text display on the combat log reading \"Confused\".\nFor defenses against the &lt;a href=\"Confused\"&gt;Confused&lt;/a&gt; status effect, see the linked article.\nThe Chaos spell specifically can also be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Enchantment&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe spell is similar to the lower 4th level arcane spell &lt;a href=\"Confusion\"&gt;Confusion&lt;/a&gt;; however, this spell has a larger &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; penalty.\nTrivia.\nThe &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Chaos_%28Wizard_Spell%29\"&gt;Advanced D&amp;D 2nd Edition - Chaos (Wizard Spell)&lt;/a&gt; behaves differently than the one implemented by Bioware, with more random and chaotic variable effects occurring.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has moved this spell from a 5th to 7th level tier. Its casting time, effects, duration and description are also changed. See below:\nChaos\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Enchantment\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 7\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Spell negates\nThis spell allows the caster to create a sphere of chaotic magic. All enemies within the area affected by the casting of this spell must make a saving throw vs. spell at -4 for every round that they remain in the sphere, and if the save is failed one of the following random effects occurs: the target goes berserk, becomes confused, becomes paralyzed, is rendered unconscious, or flees in panic."}
{"id": "51793", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51793", "title": "Chaos (Creature)", "text": "Chaos is a chaotic evil spirit that can coalesce and manifest into a Mist creature. It is encountered as part of the Druid stronghold quest line. It will be encountered on the outskirts of &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; and cajoled forth from the boy &lt;a href=\"Loren\"&gt;Loren&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThe party druid will be assigned a task by the &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20of%20the%20Grove\"&gt;Spirit of the Grove&lt;/a&gt; to help Loren exorcise an intruding spirit from his mind. The party will find Loren in the southern outskirts of Trademeet. Speak with the boy. Through force of will and dialogue, force the spirit to engage.\nWhen asked, \"Why do you torment this boy?\" the fell spirit replies, \"He is ours! Cursed Marek thought to fight us but we are the Dark Power, the Eternal Power of nature's chaos. We cannot be defeated! They boy will not follow in Marek's footsteps! Feel true power, druid!\"\nOnce the spirit has been forced to reveal itself from Loren's mortal frame, the spirit swirls and forms into a creature of pure evil and entropy. The party must now defeat it by physical or magical means and destroy it.\nIn battle, the monster will engage in melee combat if any near to close quarters combat with it. Be careful of its &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; attack.\nThe Chaos creature will attempt spell casting, as noted in the scripted spells listed in the InfoBox. All of those will be attempted sequentially. Spell casts and melee attacks might be occurring in the same round due to scripting.\nAttention to the immunities and regeneration rate of this opponent - see the InfoBox.\nAs this creature has equipped the &lt;a href=\"Boots%20of%20Phasing\"&gt;Boots of Phasing&lt;/a&gt;, during a battle it will exhibit an erratic and frequent jumping around the map to different opponents. Consistent with the creature's name, it is very chaotic. These boots aren't dropped or obtainable if the monster is destroyed.\nNotes.\nNot a Bug per se, but the creature uses a Fighter/Mage script for its spell casting use - however, the creature file has no mage class experience level assigned. This is not ideal and can lead to less-than-optimal spell potency for the monster.\nThe creature has an always on Blur animation, but it isn't an actual &lt;a href=\"Blur\"&gt;Blur&lt;/a&gt; spell effect, it is just for visual purposes.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some changes to this creature. A new default Fighter/Mage script is assigned with a \"Smarter Mage AI. SCS changes the creature's class to Fighter/Mage with a level 12/12 experience level. A different memorized spell book is available to the monster.\nWhen it becomes hostile the following instantly cast spells are launched: &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;.\nWith a F/M class, the creature has a modestly improved &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt;. SCS also furnishes the creature with a small &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Electricity%20damage\"&gt;Electricity damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance. Also, as a Fighter it gets a constitution HP bonus to 128 HP.\nExpect a &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Lightning\"&gt;Chain Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Melf%27s%20Acid%20Arrow\"&gt;Melf's Acid Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, and many other spells during this fight."}
{"id": "9074", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9074", "title": "Chaos Blade", "text": "&lt;a href=\"Haer%27Dalis\"&gt;Haer'Dalis&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0joins the party dual wielding &lt;a href=\"Entropy\"&gt;Entropy&lt;/a&gt; and Chaos Blade.\nChaos Blade gives -2 penalty to target's &lt;a href=\"dexterity\"&gt;dexterity&lt;/a&gt; on hit, no save, no cure, for 5 &lt;a href=\"Game%20Terminology%23R\"&gt;rounds&lt;/a&gt;, the effects are cumulative.\nThis shortsword is only usable by Haer'Dalis. In the \"\", even rogues with &lt;a href=\"Use%20Any%20Item\"&gt;Use Any Item&lt;/a&gt; may not wield it."}
{"id": "4819", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4819", "title": "Chaos Shield", "text": "Chaos Shield is one of the three spells exclusive to the &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Mage\"&gt;Wild Mage&lt;/a&gt;. It increases the odds that the mage will successfully cast the spell they intended in the way they intended even during a wild surge.\nThere is no scroll for this spell included in the game.\nGameplay.\nThis spell is applied to the caster only.\nAfter the spell is cast a 3D graphic effect plays over the caster's sprite, and sound effect is audibled.\nWhile the spell is active, the character's portrait will display an icon (No. 163) titled \"Chaos Shield\".\nThe spell adjusts the caster's probability of gaining a favorable result when a &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Surge\"&gt;Wild Surge&lt;/a&gt; occurs, by applying a set 15% bonus.\nA wild surge bonus of 15 can be thought as a combination of two desirable things:\nNote that this spell won't stack with itself, nor with the &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Chaos%20Shield\"&gt;Improved Chaos Shield&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Robe%20of%20Goodman%20Hayes\"&gt;Robe of Goodman Hayes&lt;/a&gt;, as they all set the base value for the mage's &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Surge%23Mechanics\"&gt;wild surge bonus&lt;/a&gt;, but don't add to each other in a cumulative manner.\nChaos Shield can be removed by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects as well as a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, changing its duration, and effects. See below for description:\nChaos Shield\nLevel: 2\nSchool: None\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 2 rounds/level\nCasting Time: 2\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nChaos Shield increases a wild mage\u2019s chance to gain a favorable result when a wild surge occurs. Every time a roll is made on the wild surge chart, an extra 15 is added to the dice roll. When Nahal\u2019s Reckless Dweomer is cast, the bonus from Chaos Shield stacks with the wild mage\u2019s level bonus."}
