{"id": "13073", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13073", "title": "Important Events", "text": "Important Events is the &lt;a href=\"journal\"&gt;journal&lt;/a&gt; entry that logs your progress through the of \"\". As befits its role in the game, Important Events is always the top item in the current &lt;a href=\"quests\"&gt;quests&lt;/a&gt; section of your journal. Don't assume that this means that whatever directions it gives should be the first thing you should do. Side quests are an important and necessary part of the game.\nPrologue.\nThe first &lt;a href=\"journal\"&gt;journal&lt;/a&gt; entry is acquired right after completing the &lt;a href=\"character%20generation\"&gt;character generation&lt;/a&gt;. It remains the only Important Event during the &lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt;.\nFind Gorion.\n&lt;a href=\"Find%20Gorion\"&gt;Find Gorion&lt;/a&gt; points to &lt;a href=\"Gorion\"&gt;Gorion&lt;/a&gt; and summarizes what otherwise can be learnt by speaking with him, giving advice what should be done before leaving &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt;.\nChapter One.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20One\"&gt;Chapter One&lt;/a&gt;, several events are possible, with their exact number depending on the path taken.\nGo to the Friendly Arm Inn.\n&lt;a href=\"Go%20to%20the%20Friendly%20Arm%20Inn\"&gt;Go to the Friendly Arm Inn&lt;/a&gt; resumes &lt;a href=\"Gorion\"&gt;Gorion&lt;/a&gt;'s words, spoken immediately before leaving &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt;, and is automatically obtained in the morning after the events that followed the departure.\n&lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is free to choose a different path and heading south to &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt; without visiting the Arm first, for example on behalf of &lt;a href=\"Xzar%20and%20Montaron\"&gt;Xzar and Montaron&lt;/a&gt;. In this case the following event will happen at any later point of time, if Khalid and Jaheira are finally met and the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt; not yet been cleared.\nMeet with Khalid &amp; Jaheira.\n&lt;a href=\"Meet%20with%20Khalid%20%26amp%3B%20Jaheira\"&gt;Meet with Khalid &amp; Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; reminds &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;, when reaching the &lt;a href=\"Friendly%20Arm%20Inn\"&gt;Friendly Arm Inn&lt;/a&gt;, that there may be two friends waiting inside the &lt;a href=\"The%20Friendly%20Arm\"&gt;inn&lt;/a&gt;.\nVisiting the Arm and Khalid and Jaheira is still possible after having reached Nashkel, but the both will be gone when &lt;a href=\"%23Chapter%20Three\"&gt;Chapter Three&lt;/a&gt; has begun, after solving the issues in the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;.\nTravel to Nashkel.\nAfter the &lt;a href=\"Meet%20with%20Khalid%20%26amp%3B%20Jaheira\"&gt;meeting&lt;/a&gt;, wether &lt;a href=\"Khalid\"&gt;Khalid&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; join the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; or not, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; decides to &lt;a href=\"travel%20to%20Nashkel\"&gt;travel to Nashkel&lt;/a&gt;.\nChapter Two.\nDuring &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Two\"&gt;Chapter Two&lt;/a&gt;, the Important Events follow a rather straight path.\nSpeak to the Mayor of Nashkel.\n&lt;a href=\"Speak%20to%20the%20Mayor%20of%20Nashkel\"&gt;Speak to the Mayor of Nashkel&lt;/a&gt; is received as soon as the party arrives either at Nashkel or at its mines for the first time \u2013 which simultaneously opens Chapter Two.\nThe mayor, &lt;a href=\"Berrun%20Ghastkill\"&gt;Berrun Ghastkill&lt;/a&gt;, will especially react to the presence of Jaheira, Khalid, &lt;a href=\"Xzar\"&gt;Xzar&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Montaron\"&gt;Montaron&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 in that order \u2013 in the party when spoken to initially.\nVisit the Nashkel Mines.\nAfter having spoken with Ghastkill \u2013 no matter the Ward's choice of whether helping out or not, whether for a reward or for none, Important Events will be updated as to &lt;a href=\"visit%20the%20Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;visit the Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;.\nEnter the Nashkel Mines.\nWhen visiting the mines, though only after having spoken to Nashkel's mayor, another update to the Important Events is received, &lt;a href=\"Enter%20the%20Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Enter the Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Nashkel Mines.\nThe owner of the mines, &lt;a href=\"Emerson\"&gt;Emerson&lt;/a&gt;, can be found opposite of the \"Entrance to the Mines\" \u2013 which is blocked by three &lt;a href=\"Amnian%20Soldier%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Amnian soldiers&lt;/a&gt; who don't allow access until permitted. Speaking with him will update the Events for the entry &lt;a href=\"The%20Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;The Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;.\nDemons in the Mines.\nUpon reaching the mines' second subterranean level, the party is approached by &lt;a href=\"miner%20Beldin\"&gt;miner Beldin&lt;/a&gt;. He asks for help against \"yipping demons\" which leads to the next Important Event, &lt;a href=\"Demons%20in%20the%20Mines\"&gt;Demons in the Mines&lt;/a&gt;; those &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s, however, turn out to be actually &lt;a href=\"kobold\"&gt;kobold&lt;/a&gt;s.\nChapter Three.\n&lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Three\"&gt;Chapter Three&lt;/a&gt; starts after picking up &lt;a href=\"Tazok\"&gt;Tazok&lt;/a&gt;'s letters to &lt;a href=\"Mulahey\"&gt;Mulahey&lt;/a&gt;, especially the &lt;a href=\"Note%20for%20Mulahey%20%282%29\"&gt;second one&lt;/a&gt;.\nReturn to Nashkel.\nAfter having learned about some of the backgrounds behind the &lt;a href=\"Contaminated%20Iron\"&gt;contaminated iron&lt;/a&gt; from the Nashkel mines, Gorion's Ward is supposed to &lt;a href=\"return%20to%20Nashkel\"&gt;return to Nashkel&lt;/a&gt; and deliver the information to Berrun Ghastkill.\nThis also adds &lt;a href=\"Confronting%20Tranzig\"&gt;Confronting Tranzig&lt;/a&gt; as the first quest for Chapter Three to the journal.\nTranzig.\nReporting to the mayor only confirms that the next step would be to look for this &lt;a href=\"Tranzig%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Tranzig&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Bandits.\nWhen confronting Tranzig in the upper western room at Feldepost's, no matter how with him or &lt;a href=\"Note%20for%20Tranzig\"&gt;his belongings&lt;/a&gt; is dealt with, the next Important Event is added to the journal: to go search the &lt;a href=\"The%20Bandits\"&gt;the bandits&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Wood%20of%20Sharp%20Teeth\"&gt;Wood of Sharp Teeth&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "52656", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52656", "title": "Important Events (SoD)", "text": "After completing &lt;a href=\"The%20Desperate%20Defenders\"&gt;The Desperate Defenders&lt;/a&gt; and speaking to &lt;a href=\"Khalid\"&gt;Khalid&lt;/a&gt;, there are multiple ways the bridge can be cleared:\nAttack.\nThere are several avenues to destroy the Crusaders through combat.\nThe most direct way is to simply attack the camp after entering the map. After killing most of the major figures, the minor Crusaders will retreat, and the gate to the bridge will open. This not only a difficult fight alone (Bridgefort defenders will not join in), but it bypasses a number of quests that can be worth doing, including The Missing Patrol, The Creeping Darkness, Tender of the Dead, and The Fear. Additional, the defenders strangely do not have a reaction \nIf the Bridgefort defenders are prepared, the assault can be triggered immediately, with the defenders and party attacking over the drawbridge, a difficult fight at best.\nAlternatively, the party can return to the Flaming Fist camp, gather the army and attack from one side while the defenders attack from the other. can opt to lead the Fist attack or return to Bridgefort and lead their attack.\nIf leads the Bridgefort defenders, they can begin the conversation to surrender, and after the terms are decided, can launch a surprise attack, with or without the Flaming Fist's assistance, depending on if they were placed on alert.\nOnce the camp has been completely cleared, the barricade to the bridge opens and the next phase begins.\nSurrender / \"Surrender\".\nSince the Crusade is only interested in the supplies, either or Khalid can negotiate with The Barghest for the freedom of the defenders in return for the supplies. If Jegg has been properly prepared, she will quietly sabotage the supplies, leaving nothing for the Crusade.\nThe Bridge.\nOnce the Crusaders have been dealt with one way or another, a &lt;a href=\"BDFISTM1.CRE\"&gt;Flaming Fist Mage&lt;/a&gt; will teleport in and warn that the Crusaders are placing barrels like those that destroyed the &lt;a href=\"Crossing%20Way%20Bridge\"&gt;Crossing Way Bridge&lt;/a&gt; on the Boareskyr Bridge.\nThe gate will be open, and at the midpoint of the bridge will be 4 &lt;a href=\"BDCRUBB1.CRE\"&gt;Crusader&lt;/a&gt;s, 2 &lt;a href=\"BDCRUBB2.CRE\"&gt;Crusader Archer&lt;/a&gt;s, and a &lt;a href=\"BDCRUBBM.CRE\"&gt;Crusader Mage&lt;/a&gt; who begins casting a spell to open a portal. If the mage is not killed within a certain amount of time, they will open the portal and teleport away, and any living crusaders will flee. Over time, the portal will spawn several waves of random fire-related creatures: 2 &lt;a href=\"BDMEPF01.CRE\"&gt;Fire Mephit&lt;/a&gt;s, a &lt;a href=\"BDSALF01.CRE\"&gt;Fire Salamander&lt;/a&gt;, or a &lt;a href=\"BDELFIRL.CRE\"&gt;Lesser Fire Elemental&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf any of the barrels take at least 24 points of damage (they take half damage from anything but acid, electricity, fire, and magic damage, and they normally automatically succeed on all saves), everyone on the map will be killed, and the game ends."}
