{"id": "55653", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55653", "title": "Imprisoned One", "text": "This page is to document the creature encountered known as the Imprisoned One. \nThe encounter occurs when first entering the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Imprisoned%20One\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Imprisoned One&lt;/a&gt; area.\nGameplay.\nThis entity has no visible appearance. It communicates via a projected mind connection where it imparts visions, words and emotional impressions. It has no physical form in the game.\nIt is not meant to be seen, detected, probed by spells or abilities, attacked or otherwise interacted with except through dialogue. It is invulnerable to any form of damage or harmful effect."}
{"id": "4810", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4810", "title": "Imprisonment", "text": "When a wizard casts Imprisonment, the target is permanently imprisoned deep under the earth.\nGameplay.\nThe caster can direct this spell at a single creature at a 1-foot range.\nAfter the spell is finished, the targeted creature will be surrounded by special enclosing cage 3D animation graphic that lasts for three seconds.\n2-seconds after the cage animation begins the targeted creature is actually exposed to the imprisonment spell effect - the victim then vanishes from the map, and a sound effect is audibled.\nIf a creature is imprisoned it can be brought back and freed from the effect with the &lt;a href=\"Freedom\"&gt;Freedom&lt;/a&gt; spell, as long as that spell is cast in the same map area as where the event occurred.\nWhen a creature is imprisoned, the game counts this as a death, and awards whatever the experience point value is assigned to the creature - even though it technically isn't dead. \nIf the protagonist is imprisoned, it is game over. There is no opportunity allowed to cast a freedom spell and bring the bhaalspawn back.\nThere is &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment%20%28Trap%20the%20Soul%29\"&gt;another version&lt;/a&gt; of Imprisonment that is an innate spell (SPIN788.spl). This version is nearly the same, but it has a 10' range and a casting time of only 1. That version is typically reserved for &lt;a href=\"Demilich%20%28Watcher%27s%20Keep%29\"&gt;Demilich&lt;/a&gt; creatures to use, although some of these undead mages also use the ordinary arcane Imprisonment spell as well.\nThe wizard spell version of Imprisonment is not flagged as a \"Hostile\" spell, yet some other versions of the spell are. This inconsistency could be an error.\nNote.\nIn the classic version of the game, the imprisonment spell (and many other level 9 spells) is not meant for the player to have access to in . No imprisonment spell scroll is available until the .\nPotential protection vs Imprisonment.\nThese protections work if applied any time before the Imprisonment spell projectile hits. Once it has hit and the cage animation starts playing, it is too late - a last-second application of &lt;a href=\"Avoid%20Death\"&gt;Avoid Death&lt;/a&gt;, for example, will not save the character.\nAs with all touch spells, walking out of range once it starts casting will not help. If the target was in range when the caster started casting, the projectile will follow them everywhere.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset Wizard Spell \"Imprisonment\" is a reversible spell, and that is known as \"Freedom\". The Pen and Paper game doesn't list Freedom as its own standalone spell, it is always connected to knowing Imprisonment.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell description. See below:\nImprisonment\nLevel: 9\nSchool: Abjuration\nRange: Short\nDuration: Permanent\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen the Imprisonment spell is cast the target creature becomes entombed in a small sphere far beneath the surface of the earth in a state of suspended animation, conscious of its fate. The victim remains there unless the reverse of the spell, Freedom, is cast. Otherwise, the victim will remain there as long as the earth exists, rather a horrible fate, actually. If a Freedom spell is cast in the area where the creature was imprisoned, then he will reappear exactly where he was last standing. Dispel magic will not free creatures trapped in this manner. The target\u2019s magic resistance, if any, does not affect this spell."}
{"id": "56201", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56201", "title": "Imprisonment (Trap the Soul)", "text": "When a demilich casts the innate spell Imprisonment (Trap the Soul), a projectile is launched at the target, and then after a few moments the victim disappears from the map, sequestered away somewhere beneath the rock and soil below.\nGameplay.\nUpon the culmination of the near instantly cast spell, and the projectile striking the target, a lighting effect will play over the victim, and a sound effect will be audibled.\nThe targeted creature will vanish from the map, along with all their carried belongings.\nThere is no saving throw against this spell, nor will &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; affect it.\nThis spell can be blocked by:\nAs this ability is only used by undead, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Undead\"&gt;Protection From Undead&lt;/a&gt; scrolls can prevent being targeted by it, though it does not technically protect against the effect.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is the victim of this spell, it is game over.\nOther party members/creatures imprisoned can be liberated and returned if the &lt;a href=\"Freedom\"&gt;Freedom&lt;/a&gt; spell is cast in the same area as the imprisonment.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; retitles this spell as \"Demilich Trap the Soul\".\nInstead of imprisonment, it will apply a &lt;a href=\"Maze\"&gt;Maze&lt;/a&gt; effect, with a save vs. Spells with a -4 penalty to prevent being sent to a planar maze.\nWhether the saving throw is achieved or not, the target is &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drained&lt;/a&gt; 4 experience levels."}
{"id": "4685", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4685", "title": "Improved Alacrity", "text": "Improved Alacrity is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability (HLA)&lt;/a&gt; usable by &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer\"&gt;Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt; classes.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell ability to self only.\nUpon completion of the spell, the caster will show a brief 3D graphic effect rendered on their sprite.\nThe player character will show an icon (No. 159) titled \"Improved Alacrity\" on their portrait for the spell's duration.\nAdditionally, a sound effect is audibled when the spell is cast, and another when it expires.\nThe spell implements an effect called \"Aura Cleansing\" on the caster for 12 seconds. It cannot be removed or dispelled.\nA party will most likely rarely face this mage HLA in any gameplay encounter in the game, except in some encounters related to Beamdog's added companions during the Throne of Bhaal portion of the game. \nTo use this ability, select the \"Mage Book\" button on the character record and select the Improved Alacrity spell icon.\nThe spell's casting time is 9. If successful, the combat log will display a text reading \"&lt;CHARACTER&gt; Improved Alacrity\" - the two round alacrity period has now begun.\nFor the next two rounds, the caster may attempt as many spell casts as possible within the restrictions of the two-round period, one after the next, with each completed spell showing a screen text displaying the cast spell's name followed by \"Aura Cleansed\".\nNormal Casting.\nSpell casting time is measured in ticks, each of which are 1/10 of a round, or 0.6 seconds. A frame is 1/30 of a second, which means there are 18 frames per tick and 180 frames per round.\nNormally, casters can only cast one spell per round and must wait until the beginning of the next round to cast their next spell. Casting begins at tick 0; once a number of ticks have passed equal to the spell's casting time, the spell is released, and the caster must wait until tick 0 of the next round until they can cast again. If a spell or ability has a cast time of 0 (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Barbarian%20Rage\"&gt;Barbarian Rage&lt;/a&gt; in , or casting &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt; while wearing the &lt;a href=\"Amulet%20of%20Power\"&gt;Amulet of Power&lt;/a&gt;), it will go off immediately - more specifically, after 1 frame has passed - and is therefore rarely interrupted.\nFor example, a wizard casting &lt;a href=\"Skull%20Trap\"&gt;Skull Trap&lt;/a&gt; at the beginning of combat: \nImproved Alacrity Casting.\nWhile Improved Alacrity is active, spells can be cast as soon as the current spell is finished, allowing multiple spells to be cast in a single round.\nInteraction with Improved Casting Time.\nThe total potential spells cast per round under Improved Alacrity is greatly increased while wearing items that improve &lt;a href=\"Game%20Terminology%23C\"&gt;casting time&lt;/a&gt;, e.g. the &lt;a href=\"Robe%20of%20Vecna\"&gt;Robe of Vecna&lt;/a&gt; (cast time improved by 4).\nExamples Comparing Potential Damage Output.\nExample 1, Level 20 Sorcerer, No Alacrity.\nAverage Single-Target Damage Dealt in 3 rounds formula_1 330 damage\nExample 2, Level 20 Sorcerer, Improved Alacrity.\nThe average damage dealt in 3 rounds formula_1 525 damage. Damage output is almost twice that dealt in Example 1 (without Improved Alacrity), while only using one Level 9 spell slot.\nExample 3, Level 20 Sorcerer with Improved Alacrity, wearing Robe of Vecna and Amulet of Power.\nAssuming Wish Rests are successful, average damage dealt in 1 round formula_1 \"1206\" damage, and in 3 rounds formula_1 \"4256\" damage . Damage output in 1 round is more than twice that in Example 2 (with Improved Alacrity over three rounds). Total damage over 3 rounds is more than 8 times Example 2 (with Alacrity) and more than 15 times Example 1 (No Alacrity).\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this High-level class ability spell, revising its school, and description. See below:\nImproved Alacrity\nLevel: Epic\nSchool: Alteration\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 2 rounds\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nImproved Alacrity essentially erases the pause between casting spells. When cast, the mage can begin casting a new spell the instant he is finished casting his current spell. The effect lasts for 2 rounds."}
{"id": "37787", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37787", "title": "Improved Archer Kit", "text": "Improved Archer Kit is a for ', the \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20Trilogy\"&gt;Baldur's Gate Trilogy&lt;/a&gt;\" and the ' of the , including the \"\". It was created by &lt;a href=\"http%3A//forums.beamdog.com/profile/argent77\"&gt;argent77&lt;/a&gt;.\nFeatures.\nIt attempts to rebalance the &lt;a href=\"archer\"&gt;archer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"kit\"&gt;kit&lt;/a&gt;, so that low level archers don't outshine other classes, while high-level archers may still keep up with other &lt;a href=\"ranger\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt; kits. The mod adjusts overall power of the archer and adds a couple of useful skills and abilities to the kit. It also adds +4 enchanted &lt;a href=\"arrow\"&gt;arrow&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"bolt\"&gt;bolt&lt;/a&gt;s as a stand-alone component, making archery useful against high-level &lt;a href=\"enemies\"&gt;enemies&lt;/a&gt; introduced in \"\".\nContent Changes.\nImproved Archer kit.\nImproves the Archer kit by balancing stat progression and adding a couple of unique skills and abilities. This is the main component of the mod.\nAdd fighter kit: Marksman.\nInstalls the &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt; kit \"Marksman\" to the game.\nAdd paladin kit: Bow Knight.\nInstalls the &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt; kit \"Bow Knight\" to the game.\nAdd thief kit: Sharpshooter.\nInstalls the &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; kit \"Sharpshooter\" to the game.\nAdd +4 arrows, bolts and two powerful bows to the game.\nBG2, BGT, BG2:EE and EET: Adds +4 arrows and bolts to a number of stores and creatures in the ToB part of the game as well as to &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. Adds a powerful longbow somewhere to the third level of &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. Adds an even more powerful composite longbow to the outdoor area of &lt;a href=\"Sendai%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;Sendai's Enclave&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "49612", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49612", "title": "Improved Asylum", "text": "The Improved Asylum is a for ' and the '. It adds new challenges for Bodhi's part of the &lt;a href=\"Escaping%20the%20asylum\"&gt;Escaping the asylum&lt;/a&gt; plot. The new content is added to the second level of the labyrinth (&lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Bodhi%27s%20Hunt%20Level%202\"&gt;AR1513&lt;/a&gt;).\nThe original mod by author Rastor is deprecated, however the quest part was resurrected for the Enhanced Edition.\nFor more information see the links.\nComponents.\n- Main component adds another high-level adventurer party to the maze that has been caught there previously. Only one party can escape, of course.\n- Additional Spellhold Lich added to library (optional)"}
{"id": "4820", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4820", "title": "Improved Chaos Shield", "text": "Improved Chaos Shield is one of the three spells exclusive to &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Mage\"&gt;Wild Mage&lt;/a&gt;s. It increases the odds that the mage will successfully cast the spell they intended in the way they intended even during a wild surge.\nThere are no scrolls for this spell included in the game.\nGameplay.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Mage\"&gt;Wild Mage&lt;/a&gt; casts this spell upon self only.\nWhen the spell is finished, a brief 3D graphic effect renders upon the caster's sprite, and a sound effect audibles.\nA player character will show an icon (No. 162) titled \"Improved Chaos Shield\" on their portrait for the spell's duration.\nThis spell cannot be \"stacked\" with &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Shield\"&gt;Chaos Shield&lt;/a&gt; or a second application of Improved Chaos Shield - those spells and &lt;a href=\"Robe%20of%20Goodman%20Hayes\"&gt;Robe of Goodman Hayes&lt;/a&gt; all \"set\" the base value for the mage's &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Surge%23Mechanics\"&gt;wild surge bonus&lt;/a&gt;, so they are not additive/cumulative with one another.\nThe spell implements an adjustment to the chance for a \"Wild Surge\" to occur:\nA wild surge bonus of 25 can be thought as a combination of two desirable things:\nThis spell can be removed with a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell, but not by a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition has no spell titled \"Improved Chaos Shield\" in the ruleset. For a listing of the AD&amp;D Wild Magic spells and further reading, see the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Wild_Magic_%28WSC%29\"&gt;Wild Magic from the Wizard Spells Compendium&lt;/a&gt; link.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its duration, clarifies stacking effects, and description. See below:\nImproved Chaos Shield\nLevel: 7\nSchool: None\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 2 turns\nCasting Time: 7\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nImproved Chaos Shield increases a wild mage\u2019s chance to gain a favorable result when a wild surge occurs. Every time a roll is made on the wild surge chart, an extra 25 is added to the dice roll. When Nahal\u2019s Reckless Dweomer is cast, the bonus from Improved Chaos Shield stacks with the wild mage\u2019s level bonus. The caster may have only one chaos shield at a time."}
