{"id": "5825", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5825", "title": "Improved Haste", "text": "Compared to the 3rd-level spell &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt;, Improved Haste targets a single creature, does not cause fatigue when the spell duration ends, and grants the \"Improved\" Haste effect which in part, doubles &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn , this spell will notably block &lt;a href=\"Offensive%20Spin\"&gt;Offensive Spin&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to one creature only, including self if desired.\nWhen the spell cast is finished a sparkling blue projectile travels to the target and applies the spell's effect - at the same time a text is displayed reading \"Hasted\", and the target will have a 3D lighting effect, and a brief color fade rendered over their sprite.\nA player character will see an icon (No. 110) titled \"Improved Haste\" on their portrait for the spell's duration.\nA sound effect audibles when the spell is cast, and another when it expires.\nMost detailed questions about how Haste and Improved Haste effects operate are documented on the &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt; page.\nThis is one of the most useful spells available to the player in the game.\nThis spell is rarely used by enemies, where the normal Haste effect is typically cast by opponents or otherwise implemented instead.\nThe spell caps out at caster level 20, so the maximum duration available with this spell is 23 rounds.\nImproved Haste is subject to &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects.\nImproved Haste is unaffected by a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nItems which provide use of Improved Haste.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;effect&lt;/a&gt; of this spell is also granted via charges by the following items (user only):\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition ruleset also provides an \"Improved Slow\" Wizard spell. The D&amp;D 2nd Edition version of \"Improved Haste\" spell boosts dexterity by +4 as well.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, area of effect, duration and description. See below:\nImproved Haste\nLevel: 6\nSchool: Alteration\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 6\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, each affected creature functions at double normal movement rate, gains a +2 bonus to attack rolls, armor class, and saving throws vs. breath, and can make one extra attack each round. Spellcasting and spell effects are not affected. There are three major differences between the third level wizard spell Haste and this spell. The first major difference is that this spell will affect all allied creatures within its area of effect. The second major difference is that there is no period of fatigue following the expiration of the spell. Third and finally, this haste spell cannot be countered by Slow."}
