{"id": "9035", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9035", "title": "Imrae", "text": "Imrae is a &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; cleric and a handmaiden of the spider queen &lt;a href=\"Lolth\"&gt;Lolth&lt;/a&gt;. She will give you your first task in &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;. She will only appear if the party has spoken with &lt;a href=\"Solaufein\"&gt;Solaufein&lt;/a&gt; outside the &lt;a href=\"Male%20Fighters%27%20Society\"&gt;Male Fighters' Society&lt;/a&gt; first.\nGameplay.\nMeet Imrae and Solaufein on a platform near the entrance to Ust Natha. Imrae orders Solaufein to explain to the party what is needed. He'll say:\nHe'll continue based on your response: \nThe party and Solaufein are to meet at the designated place soon and rescue this eldest Matron's daughter. The event will occur in the Eastern section of the Underdark, across the Kuo-toa bridge. If the rescue is successful, this will introduce &lt;a href=\"Phaere\"&gt;Phaere&lt;/a&gt; into the story.\nReturn to speak with Imrae after the rescue mission for further dialogue and direction to continue the quest line.\nNote.\nShould the party ever make Imrae hostile, then this will cause the drow city script to launch, turning the entire Ust Natha city hostile and removing Adalon's illusionary disguise. If that occurs the Jig is up, and the party has failed its mission. "}
