{"id": "21478", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21478", "title": "Instant Game Over", "text": "Actions performed by friendly NPCs or potential enemies that end the game by forcing the protagonist into a scripted scene, in which they instantly kill the entire party. Such behaviors are triggered by aggressive moves against the NPC at undesirable plot stages or by talking into a Fermi paradox that would otherwise alter the space time consistency. In visual, the kills may come from physical contact, altered spells or other forms."}
{"id": "6270", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6270", "title": "Intelligence", "text": "Intelligence is one of the six &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores\"&gt;ability scores&lt;/a&gt;. It is the prime requisite of &lt;a href=\"mages\"&gt;mages&lt;/a&gt;, and as such requires a score of 15 to &lt;a href=\"dual-class\"&gt;dual-class&lt;/a&gt; from mage to another class and a score of 17\u00a0to dual-class from another class to mage.\nIntelligence is especially important to &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;specialist mages&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Mage\"&gt;wild mages&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"bard\"&gt;bard&lt;/a&gt;s. Although &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;s are commonly grouped with other wizards, they do not gain any special benefits from INT.\n&lt;a href=\"Gnome\"&gt;Gnome&lt;/a&gt;s have a +1 INT bonus, allowing them to start with 19 INT; &lt;a href=\"Half-Orc\"&gt;Half-Orc&lt;/a&gt;s have a -2 INT penalty, limiting them to 16 INT at the start of the game.\nEffects.\nMages and Bards Only.\nMages and Bards (and Sorcerers) do NOT gain more spell slots from higher Intelligence. Spell slot increases only happen for &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druids&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cleric\"&gt;Clerics&lt;/a&gt; with high &lt;a href=\"Wisdom\"&gt;Wisdom&lt;/a&gt;.\nScores table.\nBased on the and ."}
{"id": "52957", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52957", "title": "Intelligence (BG3)", "text": "Intelligence (INT) is one of the six &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Ability Scores&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20III\"&gt;Baldur's Gate III&lt;/a&gt;\". It represents a creature's memory and mental power. It affects skill rolls for &lt;a href=\"Arcana%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Arcana&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"History%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;History&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Investigation%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Investigation&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Nature%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Nature&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Religion%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Religion&lt;/a&gt;. It is also the primary ability of &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Wizards&lt;/a&gt;, being used for their spellcasting success rolls."}
