{"id": "22697", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22697", "title": "Intrigue with Jarlaxle", "text": " There's a One-day time limit in this quest. Failure to obey the time limit nullifies the Gilded Rope's ability to deactivate the tower wards.\nIntrigue with Jarlaxle is a side quest available in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%205\"&gt;chapter 5&lt;/a&gt;.\nAquisition.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;, after the meeting with &lt;a href=\"Matron%20Mother%20Ardulace%20Despana\"&gt;Matron Mother Ardulace Despana&lt;/a&gt;, a solitary mage figure named &lt;a href=\"Visaj\"&gt;Visaj&lt;/a&gt; appears on the path just north of &lt;a href=\"Deirex%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Deirex's Tower&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0He initiates dialogue when the party is close by and proposes to sell a &lt;a href=\"Gilded%20Rope\"&gt;Gilded Rope&lt;/a&gt; for . \nVisaj explains that the rope has been stolen from &lt;a href=\"Jarlaxle\"&gt;Jarlaxle&lt;/a&gt;, and it has an enticing use - \".. with it, you would be immune to Deirex's power and could loot the mage tower as you pleased! Consider the possibilities!\".\nIf &lt;a href=\"Viconia%20DeVir\"&gt;Viconia DeVir&lt;/a&gt; is a party member she has in interjection in Visaj's lines of dialogue saying \"I know of this drow. An infamous mercenary, leader of the Bregan D'aerthe,, a powerful rogue known throughout the Underdark.\"\nif you don't have that much gold, he'll sell just it for . If the PC's &lt;a href=\"charisma\"&gt;charisma&lt;/a&gt; is 15 or higher, the party can talk him down to - or threaten him and take the rope from him for free.\nThe party can turn down Visaj's offer as well, and not obtain the rope. If so, then he remains at this spot and can be contacted later if the party changes its mind.\nIf the party obtains the rope, Visaj will walk away and disappear off the map afterwards. If the party is planning to attack him, see his article page for more on this subject.\nWith the rope in your possession, it just remains for the party to decide to undertake the foray into the lich's tower. If Visaj's explanation of the rope's powers are true, then it will provide immunity to the lich's power and allow the opportunity to access any treasures within. What red blooded adventurer could refuse?\nWalkthrough.\nJarlaxle's Assignment.\nThe party can now move towards Deirex's Tower and enter it. &lt;a href=\"Deirex\"&gt;Deirex&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt; is present within and engages your party immediately with a short dialogue and then via a cut scene, casting what appears to be an Imprisonment Spell. Fortunately, and surprisingly, you are instead teleported to Jarlaxle's pocket dimension conference room.\u00a0\nJarlaxle will say:\nIt is apparent that Jaraxle knows who the bhaalspawn is, and the drow illusion is not sufficient to fool him. He continues his explanation of what is going on (with interjections from Visaj) and will answer some questions. The party learns that &lt;a href=\"Deirex%27s%20Gems\"&gt;gems&lt;/a&gt; are required to be taken from the lich, as these contain the trapped souls of his men. He says:\nHe proposes that the party get moving on the gem recovery ASAP, saying:\nIn the end, after Visaj replies, he gives you one day to accomplish this task. \nDeirex has apparently trapped the souls of some of Jarlaxle's men in those gems. Whether you agree or not, he teleports you back to Ust Natha. It is up to you if you enter the lich's Tower to take on Jarlaxle's \"request\". See the &lt;a href=\"Deirex\"&gt;Deirex&lt;/a&gt; article page for his statistics and capabilities. \nEnter the Tower and you'll soon have to fight with Deirex, who is capable of casting &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Abi-Dalzim%27s%20Horrid%20Wilting\"&gt;Abi-Dalzim's Horrid Wilting&lt;/a&gt; and puts up a potentially stiff resistance (). Be sure to search his body for the &lt;a href=\"Lich%27s%20Tooth\"&gt;Lich's Tooth&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Jae%27llat%20Wardstone\"&gt;Jae'llat Wardstone&lt;/a&gt;. Also search this place for treasures (some of which are trapped), including:\nTaking Deirex's Gems will instantly teleport you back to the pocket dimension. So, ensure you take these gems last, or you will potentially miss out on the other valuables. Once again in the pocket plane headquarters within &lt;a href=\"Jarlaxle%27s%20House\"&gt;Jarlaxle's House&lt;/a&gt;, he and Visaj are present. Dialogue presents and Jarlaxle is pleased that those gems were found. \nJarlaxel says: \"\"And here you are, once again, with gems in hand! Really, &lt;CHARNAME&gt;, you have lived up to my expectations and then some! I'll take those gems, thank you.\"\nHe then continues: \"Ahhh, precious, aren't they? To think the Jae'llat have squirreled away such beauty for a millennium. What do you figure they'll get on the market, Visaj?\"\nVisaj replies: \"A considerable amount, Commander. There are more than a few nobles who would pay dearly for the opportunity to vex the Jae'llat, regardless of their worth.\"\nJaraxel then says: \"True enough. I wish I could be there to see the matron mother's face when she finds out we got our payment anyway.\"\nAt this point, Gorion's Ward exclaims \"Wait a minute! I thought you said those gems contained the souls of your men!\"\" - if &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Haer%27Dalis\"&gt;Haer'Dalis&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Nalia%20de%27Arnise\"&gt;Nalia de'Arnise&lt;/a&gt; are party members then one of those companions will make a version of this exclamation instead.\nJarlaxel explains: \"\"Would I risk my men against the lich? I just wanted the payment I was due, as well as collecting the price of the matron mother's insult to the Bregan D'aerthe.\"\nHe continues: \"I have not only collected the soul gems of the matron who founded the Jae'llat, but you killed their ally Deirex, a member of their own House. I have collected for myself one of the most valuable possessions that the Jae'llat had... the soul gems of the matron who founded their clan. - I think matters between the Bregan D'aerthe and House Jae'llat are pretty much even now, wouldn't you agree, &lt;CHARNAME&gt;?\"\"\nAt this stage of the dialogue, the party has some reply selections it can make, but they boil down to two outcomes.\nThe first is to willingly or begrudgingly accept what has occurred, and if so, the party will hear some final remarks and explanations of just what can be done to raid &lt;a href=\"House%20Jae%27llat\"&gt;House Jae'llat&lt;/a&gt; using the &lt;a href=\"Jae%27llat%20Wardstone\"&gt;Jae'llat Wardstone&lt;/a&gt;, and that Jarlaxel will ensure that the city will not intervene - and also that the party is free to return to &lt;a href=\"Deirex%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Deirex's Tower&lt;/a&gt; and use the &lt;a href=\"Lich%27s%20Tooth\"&gt;Lich's Tooth&lt;/a&gt; to pass into the tower's inner treasury.\nIf the party goes with this decision, they'll receive () for their daring mission, and .\nAlternatively, Gorion's Ward can say \"\"But you and I are not even. I am not one of your lackeys, and I demand payment!\" - and Jarlaxle will then reply - \"But I am allowing you to keep your little secret, &lt;PRO_RACE&gt;. Is that worth nothing to you? Dance amongst the drow as long as you wish; I care not - As for what you choose to make of your encounter with me, that is up to you. You may choose to be bitter, or you can take advantage of your situation.\"\"\nThe party then has the &lt;a href=\"Gilded%20Rope\"&gt;Gilded Rope&lt;/a&gt; removed, but also receives an additional .\nSome parting remarks are made and the party is transported back to the exterior of Deirex's Tower.\nThe second choice is to not accept how Jarlaxel has taken advantage of the party, and to threaten him repeatedly, for example, \"\"I'll kill you for trying to manipulate me!\", and after he warns you to let it go, he'll say - \"You do remember that my men are not imprisoned... we are able to protect ourselves from the likes of you. Do you truly wish to pursue this foolishness?\"\nIf the party persists and says \"I'm going to kill you, drow, and nothing's going to stop me!\"\nWith this tone and conviction, Jaraxel will say \"A shame. Your funeral.\"\"\nAnd with that, both the drow turn hostile and attack the party, to the death. \nWith this action the party receives no reward money or quest experience points, however the combat XP for Visaj and Jaraxel can be had, and if the party is quick enough their bodies can be looted before being transferred from the pocket plane conference room.\nIn any case, you will be teleported back to the Ust Natha pathway outside the tower. \nThe quest journal also resolves with:\nThus ends the side quest.\nInside Deirex's Tower.\nIf the party is in possession of the &lt;a href=\"Lich%27s%20Tooth\"&gt;Lich's Tooth&lt;/a&gt;, then it is now possible to bypass the wards to another doorway of Deirex's Tower into the &lt;a href=\"Deirex%27s%20Cave\"&gt;Deirex's Cave&lt;/a&gt; area. Enter and find the lich's other treasures (x 3475 y 2730), within a pool of water, including:\nHouse Jae'llat.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Jae%27llat%20Wardstone\"&gt;Jae'llat Wardstone&lt;/a&gt; in your possession, you may now bypass the magical wards against intrusion and enter &lt;a href=\"House%20Jae%27llat\"&gt;House Jae'llat&lt;/a&gt;, the wardstone will open two warded doors and allow you entrance (x 3260, y 1460). Using the wardstone to enter the house is an optional action, and the player can refrain from entering the area at all if they desire.\nIf entry to the house is undertaken, then of course this will lead to a fairly large battle against many drow warriors and spell casters, including a mage and at least two priestesses (each worth () - it just wouldn't be a drow House without those elements, and this is only the first battle, there is another one when moving to the lower platforms, which involves &lt;a href=\"Hindra%20Jae%27llat\"&gt;Hindra Jae'llat&lt;/a&gt; () and &lt;a href=\"Ist%27tar%20Jae%27llat\"&gt;Ist'tar Jae'llat&lt;/a&gt; (). If you succeed in taking down the occupants, search the place for treasure, detailed on the &lt;a href=\"House%20Jae%27llat\"&gt;House Jae'llat&lt;/a&gt; page.\nBugs.\nIf you return to Ust Natha after taking the dragon eggs from the temple of Lolth, Jarlaxle will still refer to you by your pseudonym. Retrieving &lt;a href=\"Deirex%27s%20Gems\"&gt;Deirex's Gems&lt;/a&gt; will teleport you back to the pocket dimension into a tower \u2014 from which Jarlaxle will disappear soon after, leaving you unable to escape. Unfortunately, the game files will allow this to happen. Best to finish this questline before taking the Dragon Eggs to ensure no continuity problems."}
{"id": "54168", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54168", "title": "Inventory", "text": "\"Inventory\" may refer to the player character's inventory, a &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; member's inventory, or any other creature's inventory. Only the party member's inventories are accessible during the game though, not counting cases of partial access such as pickpocketing someone, dealing with them in some manner through dialogue (getting quest rewards, buying/selling items), or killing them in order to loot their belongings.\nThe game sometimes refers to a player character's inventory as a \"pack\" or backpack on occasion, although this isn't everything the inventory manages. Everything a creature has equipped or is in its possession is being handled through its inventory, and various effects of them on the creature can be observed there, like a breakdown of the current &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"damage\"&gt;damage&lt;/a&gt; potential. The max and current hit points, the total weight currently being carried and the max weight before being encumbered are also shown there, as well as the party's amount of gold coins.\nThe inventory is a series of slots and spaces available to allocate objects or stacks of objects. Objects are also \"items\".\nParty member inventory.\nThe inventory is accessed on the individual party member record screen. There is quite a bit of information on this screen, but here is where \"item management\" takes place. The screen allows the display of those items to be viewed, selected, sorted, changed, and moved about. \nFrom the player's party game screen/combat display select the desired party member to inspect and then click on the Inventory Icon on the left side of the screen, or just press the \"I\" key. This will open another screen - the \"Inventory Screen\".\nOn the screen there are several categories of inventory slots:\nQuiver: 3 slots - For different ammunition types such &lt;a href=\"Arrow\"&gt;Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bolt\"&gt;Bolt&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Bullet\"&gt;Bullet&lt;/a&gt;. One stack of each type per slot.\nQuick Weapons: Up to 4 Slots (Determined by character class) - For different weapon types, such &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword\"&gt;Long Sword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff\"&gt;Quarterstaff&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Crossbow\"&gt;Heavy Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;. One weapon per slot.\nQuick Items: 3 slots - for certain consumable items such as a &lt;a href=\"Wand\"&gt;Wand&lt;/a&gt;, potion, or a scroll. Potions and scrolls with a stacking quantity assigned can be placed here. \nGold (gold coins icon): Shows the &lt;a href=\"Gold%20Piece\"&gt;Gold Piece&lt;/a&gt; quantity possessed by the party in total.\nBackpack (pack/bag icon): 16 total slots to store any item {or stacks of an item if they have a stacking quantity rating) - such as &lt;a href=\"Bag%20of%20Holding\"&gt;Bag of Holding&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Familiar\"&gt;Familiar&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Boo\"&gt;Boo&lt;/a&gt;, special item, book, scroll, potion, suit of armor etc.\nGround: This slot area is for viewing and moving items to and from the ground (picked up from the ground/chest/container or placed in a pile next to the selected character). There are 10 slots shown, but when there are more than ten items present in a given stockpile (pile, container etc.) then the Ground inventory has a sliding selector bar to move up or down.\nPaper Doll: In the center of the display screen is \"paper doll\" of the character, a depiction of the character's form that will reflect the worn clothing, armor and items equipped in the hands, or worn on the head and feet. It will change with any items added or subtracted from the paper doll slots.\nThe doll has the following slots available for a single item in each:\n- Torso Slot: For a suit of armor, or a robe.\n- Hands Slot: Gauntlets, bracers or gloves go here. One slot for both hands.\n- Head Slot: A helmet, Ioun stone, circlet, bandana, cowl or similar headgear would go here.\n- Neck slot: This is for a necklace, clasp, pendant, amulet and similar items worn on or near the neck.\n- Off-hand Slot: An off-hand weapon, shield, or buckler would go here. If an item in the Quick Weapons Slot requires two hands to use, then this slot can be closed off from use.\n- Right Ring Slot: a single ring, or perhaps an item such as &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Symbols\"&gt;Holy Symbols&lt;/a&gt; belong here.\n- Left Ring Slot: Same as above.\n- Waist Slot: A belt or girdle will go here.\n- Cloak Slot: A cape, shroud or cloak is placed here.\n- Feet Slot: Boots, shoes and footwear are placed here.\nSelecting/moving items.\nAny item can be selected in any of the slots discussed above with a cursor or applicable function key (depends the game platform, such as PC, Nintendo Switch, Playstation, Mobile Device). Once selected the item can be \"dragged\" to another slot such as from the off-hand to the backpack, or the Right Ring Slot to a Bag of Holding in the backpack slot.\nItems with stacks applicable can be selected, and by clicking a specific quantity from the stack selected and moved.\nMoving items between party members can be done by dragging items from the donating characters inventory screen to the recipient party members portrait. The item will always be placed in the receiving members Backpack slot. If that backpack has no empty slot, then the item won't transfer. There is a distance limitation for this function. Party members transferring items must be within that distance or they are \"too far away\".\nItems on the ground or from the \"Quick Loot Bar\" can be moved to any eligible slot, such as a found diamond to a Gem Bag, or dozen arrows to a Quiver Slot.\nCreature inventory.\nThe game's .CRE or creature files for any kind of non-player-controlled entity has a similar structure to that of the player character inventory. For example, there are quick items slots, head slot, ring slots and more. \nThis information is not visible to the player, however for the game developers, modders and users of editing tools these .CRE files can be viewed and edited. The rules for what kind of item is allowed in a specific slot can be contorted with this kind of access. For instance, &lt;a href=\"Kangaxx\"&gt;Kangaxx&lt;/a&gt; has the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Gaxx\"&gt;Ring of Gaxx&lt;/a&gt; placed in an armor slot instead of a ring slot. This prevents it from being pickpocketed yet will be available as dropped loot when the creature is defeated. "}
